WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:27.923 --> 00:01:29.664
We're screwed.

3
00:01:29.800 --> 00:01:31.837
No more free wi-fi.

4
00:01:32.970 --> 00:01:34.506
- Hey. Ki-jung!
- Yeah?

5
00:01:35.180 --> 00:01:38.799
The lady upstairs put
a password on 'iptime'.

6
00:01:39.810 --> 00:01:40.971
A password?

7
00:01:41.103 --> 00:01:42.765
Did you try 123456789?

8
00:01:42.855 --> 00:01:43.971
No luck.

9
00:01:44.064 --> 00:01:45.475
Do it the other way.

10
00:01:45.566 --> 00:01:47.148
I tried that too!

11
00:01:47.443 --> 00:01:51.232
Fuck. then we can't get WhatsApp?

12
00:01:51.322 --> 00:01:52.688
Nothing.

13
00:01:53.073 --> 00:01:54.860
Hey. Kim Ki-taek.

14
00:01:55.784 --> 00:01:59.118
Don't fucking pretend to sleep.
What do you think?

15
00:01:59.788 --> 00:02:05.455
Our phones are shut off.
Now our wifi is shut off.

16
00:02:06.295 --> 00:02:08.082
What's your plan?

17
00:02:11.800 --> 00:02:13.132
- Ki-woo.
- Yes. Dad?

18
00:02:13.218 --> 00:02:16.757
For wifi. hold it high.

19
00:02:18.182 --> 00:02:21.926
Stick it in every corner and so on.

20
00:02:25.731 --> 00:02:29.520
Damn stink bugs.

21
00:02:30.444 --> 00:02:32.606
Over here! I got it!

22
00:02:32.696 --> 00:02:34.028
Really? You got a signal?

23
00:02:34.114 --> 00:02:35.855
Yeah. see?

24
00:02:36.033 --> 00:02:38.571
This one. 'coffeeland 2G'.

25
00:02:38.786 --> 00:02:40.698
Did a new cafe open?

26
00:02:40.913 --> 00:02:42.495
Why can't I get it?

27
00:02:42.581 --> 00:02:44.163
Climb up here.

28
00:02:44.249 --> 00:02:45.535
Hey kids.

29
00:02:46.377 --> 00:02:47.993
- Does it work?
- Yeah.

30
00:02:48.087 --> 00:02:50.420
Then check WhatsApp.

31
00:02:50.923 --> 00:02:53.415
Pizza Generation said they'd contact me.

32
00:02:53.884 --> 00:02:55.170
Hold on.

33
00:02:55.761 --> 00:02:57.969
Here it is. Pizza Generation.

34
00:03:01.308 --> 00:03:04.301
Wow! Check this out. guys.

35
00:03:05.104 --> 00:03:08.313
If we go as fast as her.
we can finish today.

36
00:03:08.399 --> 00:03:09.685
Then we can get paid.

37
00:03:09.775 --> 00:03:12.893
- Should we stand up too?
- She's a pro.

38
00:03:13.320 --> 00:03:16.108
What? Fumigation?

39
00:03:18.075 --> 00:03:19.566
They still do that kind of thing?

40
00:03:19.660 --> 00:03:20.660
Guess so.

41
00:03:20.703 --> 00:03:21.536
Shut the window.

42
00:03:21.537 --> 00:03:24.029
Leave it open.
We'll get free extermination.

43
00:03:24.248 --> 00:03:25.705
Kill the stink bugs.

44
00:03:25.916 --> 00:03:28.454
Right. too many stink bugs
these days...

45
00:03:30.838 --> 00:03:32.875
God. that smells!

46
00:03:35.634 --> 00:03:37.341
I told you to shut it!

47
00:03:37.594 --> 00:03:39.381
Should I shut it. Dad?

48
00:03:50.232 --> 00:03:52.315
What exactly is the problem?

49
00:03:53.193 --> 00:03:55.936
Take this one as an example.

50
00:03:56.238 --> 00:03:58.446
You call this a straight line?

51
00:03:58.824 --> 00:04:00.656
And why's it folded here?

52
00:04:00.993 --> 00:04:02.609
Why is this sticking up?

53
00:04:02.786 --> 00:04:05.119
You didn't even fold it.

54
00:04:06.331 --> 00:04:10.291
A quarter of them look like this.

55
00:04:10.377 --> 00:04:12.869
So 1 out of 4 are rejects.

56
00:04:16.049 --> 00:04:19.793
So you're really docking
10% off our pay?

57
00:04:20.220 --> 00:04:23.713
Considering the rejects.
that's a low penalty. isn't it?

58
00:04:24.767 --> 00:04:28.351
Our pay is so low already!
How can you do this?

59
00:04:29.938 --> 00:04:31.179
Look here.

60
00:04:31.398 --> 00:04:33.856
This is not some minor issue.

61
00:04:34.026 --> 00:04:39.192
You know what one shitty box
can do to our brand image?

62
00:04:39.490 --> 00:04:42.733
Brand? You can't even afford
a box folder!

63
00:04:42.826 --> 00:04:44.237
What did you say?

64
00:04:45.204 --> 00:04:46.445
Boss.

65
00:04:47.206 --> 00:04:48.600
This is all because
of that guy. right?

66
00:04:48.624 --> 00:04:49.624
What guy?

67
00:04:49.708 --> 00:04:53.372
Your part-time worker.
He's gone AWOL. right?

68
00:04:53.587 --> 00:04:57.581
Just when the Love of God Church
made a huge group order?

69
00:04:57.841 --> 00:04:59.924
How do you know all that?

70
00:05:00.135 --> 00:05:01.626
Who told you?

71
00:05:01.970 --> 00:05:03.711
My sister knows the guy.

72
00:05:03.931 --> 00:05:08.175
He's always been a bit strange.
Got a bad reputation.

73
00:05:08.519 --> 00:05:10.306
Speaking of which. Boss.

74
00:05:11.021 --> 00:05:13.104
We'll accept a 10% penalty.

75
00:05:13.190 --> 00:05:14.226
In return...

76
00:05:14.316 --> 00:05:15.397
In return?

77
00:05:15.776 --> 00:05:18.268
Any thought of hiring
a new part-time worker?

78
00:05:18.403 --> 00:05:21.817
Sis. we need someone!

79
00:05:22.241 --> 00:05:25.359
Ditch the guy you've got now.
Just fire him.

80
00:05:26.078 --> 00:05:29.367
Tomorrow I'll come for
a formal interview. What time?

81
00:05:29.456 --> 00:05:30.947
Wait. hold on a sec.

82
00:05:31.875 --> 00:05:34.083
Let me think about it.

83
00:05:34.419 --> 00:05:37.503
Then for now.
just pay for the boxes.

84
00:05:44.263 --> 00:05:47.631
So we're all gathered here today.

85
00:05:48.183 --> 00:05:51.722
to celebrate the reconnection
of our phones.

86
00:05:51.812 --> 00:05:55.476
and this bounteous wi-fi!

87
00:05:55.566 --> 00:05:58.809
Look at that bastard.
It's not even dark yet.

88
00:06:00.946 --> 00:06:03.359
Why didn't you put up
a 'No Urinating' sign?

89
00:06:03.448 --> 00:06:04.407
I told you!

90
00:06:04.408 --> 00:06:08.778
No. signs like that
just make them piss even more.

91
00:06:09.121 --> 00:06:10.953
At least shout at him!

92
00:06:11.039 --> 00:06:12.530
Don't shout.

93
00:06:12.749 --> 00:06:14.581
"Please don't piss!"

94
00:06:16.378 --> 00:06:19.371
Hey. is that Min?

95
00:06:20.007 --> 00:06:22.169
Hey mister. that's not a toilet.

96
00:06:22.259 --> 00:06:23.625
Way to go. Min.

97
00:06:23.719 --> 00:06:25.756
Hey. punk!

98
00:06:26.346 --> 00:06:29.510
Who are you staring at. asshole?

99
00:06:29.766 --> 00:06:32.930
Come here! You little shit.

100
00:06:34.771 --> 00:06:36.888
Get a fucking grip!

101
00:06:38.108 --> 00:06:40.395
That's an impressive friend.

102
00:06:40.485 --> 00:06:43.353
College students have
a real vigor to them.

103
00:06:43.613 --> 00:06:44.613
Not like my brother.

104
00:06:44.697 --> 00:06:48.031
But is he coming here?
Did you invite him?

105
00:06:48.118 --> 00:06:49.199
No.

106
00:06:49.327 --> 00:06:50.408
Hello!

107
00:06:50.495 --> 00:06:52.031
Oh hi. Min!

108
00:06:52.372 --> 00:06:53.372
Min!

109
00:06:53.415 --> 00:06:54.248
Are you well. sir?

110
00:06:54.249 --> 00:06:56.787
- Sure.
- What are you doing here?

111
00:06:56.876 --> 00:06:58.742
I texted you. Didn't you see it?

112
00:06:59.087 --> 00:07:00.248
Sorry. were you eating?

113
00:07:00.338 --> 00:07:01.624
No. we weren't eating.

114
00:07:01.714 --> 00:07:04.001
- How are you. Ki-jung?
- Fine. you too?

115
00:07:04.092 --> 00:07:06.800
We could've met outside.
why come here?

116
00:07:06.886 --> 00:07:07.761
Because of this.

117
00:07:07.762 --> 00:07:10.550
It's for you.
but it's so heavy.

118
00:07:10.682 --> 00:07:13.015
Really? Put it down here.

119
00:07:14.978 --> 00:07:16.560
Wow. what is that?

120
00:07:16.646 --> 00:07:18.262
When I said I was meeting Ki-woo.

121
00:07:18.356 --> 00:07:21.815
my grandfather insisted
I bring this to you.

122
00:07:25.780 --> 00:07:28.113
Is this a landscape type?

123
00:07:29.367 --> 00:07:31.279
Or you can see it
as an abstract type.

124
00:07:31.369 --> 00:07:33.031
Wow. you know these!

125
00:07:33.121 --> 00:07:37.115
My grandpa has collected scholar's rocks
since his cadet days.

126
00:07:37.292 --> 00:07:40.785
Now the annex. the study.
every room in the house

127
00:07:40.879 --> 00:07:42.836
is filled with these things.

128
00:07:43.131 --> 00:07:46.920
But this stone here is said
to bring material wealth to families...

129
00:07:47.010 --> 00:07:48.251
Min!

130
00:07:48.511 --> 00:07:51.379
This is so metaphorical.

131
00:07:51.681 --> 00:07:54.890
For sure.
It's a very opportune gift.

132
00:07:54.976 --> 00:07:55.851
Of course.

133
00:07:55.852 --> 00:07:59.846
Please relay our deepest
thanks to your grandpa.

134
00:08:00.106 --> 00:08:01.893
Food would be better.

135
00:08:11.910 --> 00:08:15.074
What was that called?
A landscape stone?

136
00:08:15.205 --> 00:08:16.616
You collect those rocks too?

137
00:08:16.706 --> 00:08:21.451
Hey. thanks to that rock
I saw your parents. they look healthy.

138
00:08:23.588 --> 00:08:26.547
They're plenty healthy.
just out of work.

139
00:08:29.010 --> 00:08:31.252
Is Ki-jung taking lessons
these days?

140
00:08:32.472 --> 00:08:35.260
She can't afford lessons.

141
00:08:44.150 --> 00:08:45.607
Cute. huh?

142
00:08:46.486 --> 00:08:48.944
She's the one you're tutoring?

143
00:08:49.072 --> 00:08:51.189
Park Da-hye.
High school sophomore.

144
00:08:51.616 --> 00:08:54.780
You take over
as her English tutor.

145
00:08:55.286 --> 00:08:56.367
What do you mean?

146
00:08:56.454 --> 00:08:58.571
Tutor a rich kid.
It pays well.

147
00:08:59.707 --> 00:09:01.039
She's a nice girl.

148
00:09:01.125 --> 00:09:04.084
Look after her while
I'm studying abroad.

149
00:09:04.921 --> 00:09:08.255
What about your university friends?

150
00:09:08.466 --> 00:09:11.709
Why ask a loser like me?

151
00:09:12.262 --> 00:09:13.753
Why do you think?

152
00:09:14.389 --> 00:09:16.551
Just the thought makes me sick.

153
00:09:16.724 --> 00:09:20.889
Those disgusting frat boys
slavering over Da-hye?

154
00:09:20.979 --> 00:09:22.720
It's revolting.

155
00:09:28.736 --> 00:09:29.897
You like her?

156
00:09:34.993 --> 00:09:37.110
Hey. I'm serious.

157
00:09:38.371 --> 00:09:42.456
When she enters university.
I'll officially ask her out.

158
00:09:43.001 --> 00:09:44.958
So you take care of
her until then.

159
00:09:45.044 --> 00:09:48.708
If it's you.
I can leave in peace.

160
00:09:50.550 --> 00:09:53.293
Thanks for your trust.

161
00:09:53.720 --> 00:09:56.963
but do I have to pretend to be
a college student?

162
00:09:58.933 --> 00:10:01.721
Ki-woo. think about it.

163
00:10:02.437 --> 00:10:05.896
For years including
your military service.

164
00:10:06.065 --> 00:10:08.148
you took the university entrance
exam 4 times.

165
00:10:08.443 --> 00:10:11.402
Grammar. vocabulary.
composition. conversation...

166
00:10:11.988 --> 00:10:13.604
When it comes to English.

167
00:10:13.698 --> 00:10:18.159
you can teach 10 times better than
those drunken college pricks.

168
00:10:19.454 --> 00:10:21.912
- I guess so.
- Sure!

169
00:10:22.290 --> 00:10:25.909
But will they hire me?
I'm not a college student.

170
00:10:26.169 --> 00:10:27.626
Just fake it.

171
00:10:27.712 --> 00:10:31.422
Don't worry. you'll have
my recommendation. plus...

172
00:10:32.508 --> 00:10:34.921
How should I describe the mother...?

173
00:10:37.513 --> 00:10:38.924
She's a bit simple.

174
00:10:39.098 --> 00:10:40.259
Young and simple.

175
00:10:40.350 --> 00:10:41.557
Simple?

176
00:10:41.934 --> 00:10:43.391
What do you mean?

177
00:10:43.519 --> 00:10:47.433
Anyway. it's all good.
I had fun there.

178
00:10:48.149 --> 00:10:49.356
So you agree?

179
00:10:49.442 --> 00:10:50.899
I guess so.

180
00:10:52.195 --> 00:10:55.939
Hey. you said
your sister is artistic?

181
00:10:56.157 --> 00:10:57.898
Good at Photoshop?

182
00:11:00.536 --> 00:11:04.621
God. with skills like this.
why can't you get into art school?

183
00:11:04.707 --> 00:11:06.039
Shut up.

184
00:11:08.503 --> 00:11:10.745
Hey. no smoking in here.

185
00:11:10.838 --> 00:11:12.204
Yeah. yeah. Gimme that.

186
00:11:12.298 --> 00:11:13.414
Yeah.

187
00:11:17.887 --> 00:11:20.425
Now the cherry on top...

188
00:11:21.974 --> 00:11:26.469
Wow. does Oxford have
a major in document forgery?

189
00:11:26.771 --> 00:11:30.014
Ki-jung would be top of her class.

190
00:11:30.191 --> 00:11:32.729
She's amazing. huh?

191
00:11:32.944 --> 00:11:38.360
Our boy's going for a job interview.
Wish him luck.

192
00:11:38.908 --> 00:11:40.149
Son.

193
00:11:41.077 --> 00:11:43.820
I'm proud of you.

194
00:11:44.163 --> 00:11:45.279
Dad.

195
00:11:46.165 --> 00:11:49.158
I don't think of this
as forgery or crime.

196
00:11:49.544 --> 00:11:51.501
I'll go to this university
next year.

197
00:11:51.587 --> 00:11:54.955
So you've got a plan!

198
00:11:55.299 --> 00:11:58.838
I just printed out the document
a bit early.

199
00:12:34.505 --> 00:12:35.871
<i>Who is it?</i>

200
00:12:36.132 --> 00:12:38.124
Madame? Good afternoon.

201
00:12:38.259 --> 00:12:40.046
I'm here on Min's recommendation...

202
00:12:40.136 --> 00:12:41.877
<i>Oh right. come in.</i>

203
00:12:43.181 --> 00:12:44.547
Thank you.

204
00:13:16.047 --> 00:13:17.379
Hello!

205
00:13:18.299 --> 00:13:19.631
Hello. Madame.

206
00:13:19.801 --> 00:13:23.294
I just work here.
Come this way.

207
00:13:23.721 --> 00:13:25.337
The yard is so nice.

208
00:13:25.431 --> 00:13:27.093
The inside's nice too.

209
00:13:27.433 --> 00:13:30.801
You know the architect Namgoong?
He's famous.

210
00:13:30.978 --> 00:13:33.516
He used to live in this house.

211
00:13:35.691 --> 00:13:37.933
He designed it himself.

212
00:13:40.780 --> 00:13:45.900
As you can see.
now it's a playpen.

213
00:13:46.244 --> 00:13:47.610
This way.

214
00:13:49.747 --> 00:13:52.239
Sit yourself down here.
I'll bring the madame.

215
00:13:52.333 --> 00:13:53.540
Yes.

216
00:14:05.680 --> 00:14:06.841
<i>Madame.</i>

217
00:14:07.932 --> 00:14:09.048
<i>Madame?</i>

218
00:14:11.769 --> 00:14:12.885
Madame?

219
00:14:14.897 --> 00:14:16.138
Madame?

220
00:14:19.777 --> 00:14:21.985
He's here.
The tutoring candidate.

221
00:14:25.700 --> 00:14:27.942
I don't care about documents.

222
00:14:28.494 --> 00:14:30.907
Min recommended you. after all.

223
00:14:31.789 --> 00:14:37.660
As you know. Min is such
a brilliant human being.

224
00:14:38.421 --> 00:14:40.583
Da-hye and I were quite happy
with him.

225
00:14:40.756 --> 00:14:43.965
Regardless of her grades.
Know what I mean?

226
00:14:44.093 --> 00:14:45.254
Yes.

227
00:14:45.553 --> 00:14:47.465
He was marvelous.

228
00:14:47.555 --> 00:14:54.553
So to be honest. we wanted to stick
with him through high school.

229
00:14:55.313 --> 00:14:58.181
But all of a sudden
he's going abroad.

230
00:15:00.735 --> 00:15:06.026
Anyway. excuse me.
but if I can speak directly.

231
00:15:06.282 --> 00:15:11.118
if you're not up
to Min's level. then.

232
00:15:11.703 --> 00:15:14.161
I'm not sure
what the point is.

233
00:15:15.916 --> 00:15:19.705
So anyway.
what I want to say is.

234
00:15:20.045 --> 00:15:25.336
for your first lesson today.
do you mind if I sit in?

235
00:15:25.759 --> 00:15:29.378
I want to see it full time.
how you run your lesson.

236
00:15:31.557 --> 00:15:33.594
Is it okay with you?

237
00:16:01.962 --> 00:16:03.999
You sure about #24?

238
00:16:11.555 --> 00:16:16.220
Da-hye. you solved those later problems
then went back to #24.

239
00:16:16.518 --> 00:16:17.884
Right?

240
00:16:19.521 --> 00:16:20.762
Yes.

241
00:16:28.739 --> 00:16:33.450
If that were the first question
on a real exam. you'd be screwed.

242
00:16:34.620 --> 00:16:37.784
Look at this.
Your pulse is racing.

243
00:16:40.751 --> 00:16:43.915
The heart doesn't lie.

244
00:16:45.088 --> 00:16:48.422
An exam is like slashing through
a jungle.

245
00:16:48.592 --> 00:16:51.084
Lose that momentum
and you're finished.

246
00:16:51.512 --> 00:16:53.845
The answer to #24?
I don't care.

247
00:16:54.056 --> 00:16:59.142
Slashing through the exam.
dominating it!

248
00:16:59.853 --> 00:17:01.435
That's all I care about.

249
00:17:02.689 --> 00:17:06.103
What you need is vigor.

250
00:17:07.611 --> 00:17:08.818
Vigor.

251
00:17:10.072 --> 00:17:11.438
Understand?

252
00:17:22.417 --> 00:17:25.285
So I'll pay you
this time each month.

253
00:17:25.379 --> 00:17:28.668
3 classes a week.
2 hours each. okay?

254
00:17:29.383 --> 00:17:30.499
As for the fee.

255
00:17:30.592 --> 00:17:34.461
I was going to pay Min's rate.
then I added a bit for inflation.

256
00:17:34.555 --> 00:17:35.841
Thank you.

257
00:17:37.057 --> 00:17:39.390
How about a proper introduction?

258
00:17:39.601 --> 00:17:42.514
Da-hye's tutor.
we'll call him Kevin.

259
00:17:43.063 --> 00:17:44.725
Mr. Kevin!

260
00:17:45.148 --> 00:17:48.391
If you feel like snacking
during your lesson. just call me.

261
00:17:48.860 --> 00:17:50.897
If you need anything. ask her.

262
00:17:50.988 --> 00:17:53.526
She knows this house better than I...

263
00:17:53.657 --> 00:17:56.775
Da-song. stop it!

264
00:17:57.369 --> 00:17:58.951
I'm sorry. did he startle you?

265
00:17:59.037 --> 00:18:01.529
How cute. His name's Da-song?

266
00:18:01.623 --> 00:18:03.364
Yes. our youngest.

267
00:18:03.584 --> 00:18:05.166
Da-song. come say hi!

268
00:18:05.252 --> 00:18:06.788
This is Mr. Kevin!

269
00:18:09.047 --> 00:18:13.667
This is an Indian arrow.
I ordered it from the U.S.

270
00:18:13.760 --> 00:18:16.503
From last year he's been
an Indian fanatic.

271
00:18:18.515 --> 00:18:19.926
Indians?

272
00:18:20.684 --> 00:18:23.347
He's got a fanboy personality?

273
00:18:23.520 --> 00:18:27.184
Well. he's eccentric
and easily distracted.

274
00:18:27.274 --> 00:18:29.561
he can barely sit still!

275
00:18:30.027 --> 00:18:32.189
So last year I enrolled him
in Cub Scouts.

276
00:18:32.279 --> 00:18:35.272
hoping he'd learn moderation
and focus.

277
00:18:35.365 --> 00:18:36.776
But look.

278
00:18:37.576 --> 00:18:39.112
He's even worse.

279
00:18:41.663 --> 00:18:46.533
His scout leader is an Indian fanatic.
maybe that's why.

280
00:18:48.378 --> 00:18:51.462
The American Indian is
the very spirit of the Cub Scouts.

281
00:18:51.548 --> 00:18:52.584
It's a good thing.

282
00:18:52.674 --> 00:18:55.633
Were you a Cub Scout. Kevin?

283
00:18:55.802 --> 00:18:58.795
Sure. I'm a Scout by nature.

284
00:18:59.097 --> 00:19:03.182
Da-song is an artist by nature.
Look at this painting.

285
00:19:04.061 --> 00:19:07.020
It's so metaphorical.
It's really strong.

286
00:19:07.356 --> 00:19:08.813
Strong. right?

287
00:19:09.107 --> 00:19:11.019
You've got an eye for this.

288
00:19:12.527 --> 00:19:14.109
It's a chimpanzee. right?

289
00:19:14.196 --> 00:19:15.653
A self-portrait.

290
00:19:18.867 --> 00:19:20.278
Sure enough!

291
00:19:21.495 --> 00:19:24.863
The perspective of
a young artist eludes understanding.

292
00:19:25.040 --> 00:19:27.327
Or perhaps it's Da-song's
expressive genius...

293
00:19:27.709 --> 00:19:32.795
Anyway. we've been through
so many art teachers.

294
00:19:33.131 --> 00:19:35.339
None of them lasts even a month.

295
00:19:36.968 --> 00:19:39.927
And Da-song is just so hard
to control.

296
00:19:42.599 --> 00:19:44.932
- Just a moment. Madame.
- Yes?

297
00:19:45.352 --> 00:19:48.561
Someone just came to mind.

298
00:19:49.231 --> 00:19:50.813
What was her name?

299
00:19:51.274 --> 00:19:53.812
Jessica! Right. Jessica...

300
00:19:54.152 --> 00:19:58.237
She was in the same art school
as my cousin.

301
00:19:58.532 --> 00:20:00.899
What was her Korean name?

302
00:20:01.284 --> 00:20:06.325
Anyway. after studying applied arts
at Illinois State University.

303
00:20:06.415 --> 00:20:08.372
she returned to Korea.

304
00:20:08.458 --> 00:20:10.575
Illinois... tell me more.

305
00:20:10.919 --> 00:20:16.961
Her teaching is unusual.
but she knows how to handle kids.

306
00:20:17.676 --> 00:20:20.464
She's got a special reputation
in her field.

307
00:20:20.846 --> 00:20:23.259
But even though
her methods are unique.

308
00:20:23.348 --> 00:20:25.886
she can help kids get
into good art schools.

309
00:20:25.976 --> 00:20:30.016
Now I'm really curious.
What is she like?

310
00:20:30.272 --> 00:20:31.854
Would you like to meet her?

311
00:20:32.149 --> 00:20:35.233
Though I heard she's
in high demand...

312
00:20:41.450 --> 00:20:42.691
Hold on.

313
00:20:44.202 --> 00:20:47.741
Jessica. only child.
Illinois Chicago.

314
00:20:47.831 --> 00:20:50.699
classmate Kim Jin-mo.
he's your cousin.

315
00:20:57.841 --> 00:21:01.881
Look at how he painted the side
dishes on the tablecloth

316
00:21:02.012 --> 00:21:04.379
in this mosaic arrangement.

317
00:21:04.598 --> 00:21:07.306
But within that too.
there are repeating patterns.

318
00:21:07.476 --> 00:21:10.560
Gochujang is red. the rice...
well. anyway.

319
00:21:10.645 --> 00:21:15.561
he has a Basquiat-esque sense.
even at age 9!

320
00:21:16.026 --> 00:21:17.483
How exciting.

321
00:21:17.903 --> 00:21:22.864
I'm sure Miss Jessica
must have already sensed this.

322
00:21:23.158 --> 00:21:27.072
so I'll leave you two.
and go up for Da-hye's lesson.

323
00:21:27.871 --> 00:21:29.328
Have a nice lesson. Jessica.

324
00:21:29.498 --> 00:21:31.330
Yes. thank you for the introduction.

325
00:21:35.378 --> 00:21:40.749
So as you can see.
Da-song's eccentric genius...

326
00:21:43.512 --> 00:21:44.719
Da-hye.

327
00:21:45.055 --> 00:21:48.093
So we'll start with #38?

328
00:21:52.771 --> 00:21:53.932
Kevin.

329
00:21:54.064 --> 00:21:55.225
Yeah?

330
00:21:55.398 --> 00:22:00.314
Did you know that Da-song is
faking it all?

331
00:22:00.779 --> 00:22:03.146
Huh? What do you mean?

332
00:22:03.406 --> 00:22:05.068
It's all a show.

333
00:22:05.283 --> 00:22:09.027
Acting like a genius.
that 4th dimension stuff is all fake.

334
00:22:09.120 --> 00:22:10.827
An artist cosplay.

335
00:22:11.039 --> 00:22:12.530
Da-song?

336
00:22:13.792 --> 00:22:15.374
You know that thing.

337
00:22:15.460 --> 00:22:19.579
when he freezes and stares at the sky.
as if struck by inspiration.

338
00:22:20.257 --> 00:22:25.798
So he's walking along. then he stares
at the clouds for 10 minutes.

339
00:22:26.346 --> 00:22:28.178
So you know what I mean?

340
00:22:28.390 --> 00:22:30.882
He gives me the creeps.

341
00:22:31.059 --> 00:22:34.177
He pretends that he can't live
a normal life.

342
00:22:34.688 --> 00:22:36.270
Makes me want to puke.

343
00:22:36.356 --> 00:22:39.394
So Da-song is pretending...

344
00:22:40.151 --> 00:22:43.895
But what's that got to do
with your studies?

345
00:22:47.993 --> 00:22:51.862
Well. I'm just saying.

346
00:22:54.291 --> 00:22:56.453
Sure. so in that sense.

347
00:22:57.586 --> 00:23:01.671
what you told me
about Da-song was very interesting.

348
00:23:02.173 --> 00:23:04.039
so let's write about it
in English.

349
00:23:04.467 --> 00:23:10.304
And be sure to use the word 'pretend'
at least twice.

350
00:23:10.974 --> 00:23:14.012
Then. can I ask you a question?

351
00:23:14.102 --> 00:23:15.218
Sure.

352
00:23:15.312 --> 00:23:17.804
That teacher Jessica.

353
00:23:18.565 --> 00:23:24.562
Is she really your cousin's classmate?

354
00:23:26.823 --> 00:23:28.280
What do you mean?

355
00:23:28.533 --> 00:23:30.650
She's your girlfriend. right?

356
00:23:33.747 --> 00:23:37.787
No way... I just met her today.

357
00:23:41.838 --> 00:23:44.956
Jessica's really pretty.
isn't she?

358
00:23:45.634 --> 00:23:47.546
Aren't you interested?

359
00:23:48.720 --> 00:23:50.302
You saw her?

360
00:23:50.555 --> 00:23:54.970
Sure. she's pretty.
She's a beautiful woman.

361
00:23:55.101 --> 00:23:56.308
Yeah.

362
00:23:58.229 --> 00:24:01.097
I knew it.

363
00:24:01.983 --> 00:24:03.940
So you are interested.

364
00:24:06.738 --> 00:24:08.070
Da-hye...

365
00:24:10.617 --> 00:24:17.456
So. if we can compare Jessica
to a rose.

366
00:24:17.540 --> 00:24:19.031
then you are...

367
00:25:04.921 --> 00:25:06.583
- Let's study.
- Yes.

368
00:25:06.673 --> 00:25:11.885
Please understand that
my boy has trouble keeping still.

369
00:25:11.970 --> 00:25:13.336
I understand.

370
00:25:13.722 --> 00:25:14.963
Da-song!

371
00:25:16.224 --> 00:25:17.182
Da-song. get up!

372
00:25:17.183 --> 00:25:18.765
Come on. Da-song!

373
00:25:18.977 --> 00:25:20.684
In your butt...

374
00:25:20.770 --> 00:25:23.183
- Madame. please leave us.
- What?

375
00:25:23.690 --> 00:25:26.307
I never teach with a parent
in the room.

376
00:25:26.568 --> 00:25:28.981
But today is our first day.
and as you can see. he's...

377
00:25:29.070 --> 00:25:30.777
Wait downstairs.

378
00:25:32.240 --> 00:25:33.526
Park Da-song?

379
00:25:33.616 --> 00:25:34.732
Da-song!

380
00:25:38.747 --> 00:25:39.988
Madame?

381
00:25:41.166 --> 00:25:42.623
Want some plum extract?

382
00:25:42.709 --> 00:25:43.745
What?

383
00:25:43.918 --> 00:25:47.036
It's mixed with honey.
To ease your tension.

384
00:25:47.172 --> 00:25:49.084
Yeah. that would be great.

385
00:26:04.147 --> 00:26:05.888
- Hey.
- Yes?

386
00:26:06.274 --> 00:26:07.640
I've got an idea.

387
00:26:07.734 --> 00:26:10.898
Take two glasses of plum
extract to Da-song's room.

388
00:26:11.154 --> 00:26:14.147
You're not a parent.
so you can go in!

389
00:26:14.240 --> 00:26:15.731
Oh. that's right!

390
00:26:15.867 --> 00:26:18.951
Then I'll report back on
what's going on in there...

391
00:26:19.621 --> 00:26:21.328
Why didn't I think of it earlier?

392
00:26:23.833 --> 00:26:24.949
What?

393
00:26:25.210 --> 00:26:26.451
They came out?

394
00:26:26.961 --> 00:26:27.961
Yeah.

395
00:26:30.298 --> 00:26:33.382
So you're done already?

396
00:26:34.803 --> 00:26:36.044
Madame.

397
00:26:36.721 --> 00:26:38.678
Come sit next to me.

398
00:26:40.683 --> 00:26:42.470
Da-song. go upstairs.

399
00:26:44.395 --> 00:26:45.636
Hurry up!

400
00:26:52.153 --> 00:26:54.110
Da-song just painted this.

401
00:26:54.197 --> 00:26:55.404
I see...

402
00:26:57.075 --> 00:26:59.533
I'd rather speak with Madame alone.

403
00:26:59.828 --> 00:27:00.989
Oh. but she is...

404
00:27:01.079 --> 00:27:03.662
No. leave us.

405
00:27:08.128 --> 00:27:09.460
Madame.

406
00:27:09.671 --> 00:27:14.291
I told you I study art psychology
and art therapy?

407
00:27:14.384 --> 00:27:15.670
Yes.

408
00:27:16.344 --> 00:27:18.927
Did anything happen to Da-song
in first grade?

409
00:27:21.432 --> 00:27:23.890
To be frank.

410
00:27:24.310 --> 00:27:27.553
before I decide whether
to take on Da-song.

411
00:27:27.647 --> 00:27:30.105
I need to hear about this.

412
00:27:30.567 --> 00:27:34.527
But this is hard for me
to talk about right now.

413
00:27:34.654 --> 00:27:35.654
What to do?

414
00:27:35.655 --> 00:27:37.021
Never mind. then.

415
00:27:37.532 --> 00:27:42.744
The lower-right region of a painting is
called the 'schizophrenia zone'.

416
00:27:42.829 --> 00:27:45.321
Psychotic symptoms
often reveal themselves here.

417
00:27:45.415 --> 00:27:46.415
Oh. phrenia...

418
00:27:46.457 --> 00:27:47.457
Look here.

419
00:27:47.500 --> 00:27:49.867
Da-song painted this unusual shape.
right?

420
00:27:50.170 --> 00:27:51.377
I see.

421
00:27:53.089 --> 00:27:56.332
Over there. it's the same!
It's the same. right?

422
00:27:56.426 --> 00:27:58.292
Yes. that's correct.

423
00:27:58.720 --> 00:28:02.213
A similar shape in the same zone.
You see it now?

424
00:28:02.390 --> 00:28:03.631
Yes.

425
00:28:04.142 --> 00:28:08.307
I've stared at that painting
at every meal!

426
00:28:08.605 --> 00:28:10.722
But I had no idea.

427
00:28:10.899 --> 00:28:13.733
Calm down.
Let's compose ourselves.

428
00:28:14.444 --> 00:28:17.482
This is all a black box
into Da-song's mind.

429
00:28:18.031 --> 00:28:21.490
Would you like to
open that box with me. Madame?

430
00:28:22.577 --> 00:28:24.068
I want to open it.

431
00:28:24.162 --> 00:28:28.702
Then we'll need 4 two-hour sessions
per week.

432
00:28:28.791 --> 00:28:33.001
and this is not simple tutoring.
it's art therapy. right?

433
00:28:33.087 --> 00:28:34.087
Of course.

434
00:28:34.172 --> 00:28:37.836
Because of that my rate is
set at a very high level.

435
00:28:38.676 --> 00:28:39.676
Are you okay with that?

436
00:28:39.719 --> 00:28:41.085
It's my pleasure.

437
00:28:42.430 --> 00:28:44.342
Da-song's dad is home.

438
00:28:50.813 --> 00:28:55.228
Honey. Da-song's new art teacher
is here.

439
00:28:57.779 --> 00:28:59.862
Her name's Jessica.
from Illinois.

440
00:29:00.406 --> 00:29:02.648
<i>Jessica! This is Dong-ik.</i>

441
00:29:02.784 --> 00:29:04.491
- Hello.
- Hi.

442
00:29:04.702 --> 00:29:06.318
Thanks for your help.

443
00:29:06.537 --> 00:29:07.653
Class is over?

444
00:29:07.747 --> 00:29:08.954
Yes. just finished.

445
00:29:09.332 --> 00:29:10.664
- Driver Yoon.
- Yes?

446
00:29:10.750 --> 00:29:12.286
- Are you free?
- Yes. I am.

447
00:29:12.377 --> 00:29:14.790
Then give her a lift. okay?

448
00:29:15.088 --> 00:29:19.549
Sure. we don't want her
going down alone at night. right?

449
00:29:19.634 --> 00:29:20.750
Of course.

450
00:29:20.969 --> 00:29:22.335
Miss Jessica?

451
00:29:22.845 --> 00:29:28.386
Shall I drive you
all the way home. then?

452
00:29:29.477 --> 00:29:31.890
- Which neighborhood?
- No. that's fine.

453
00:29:31.980 --> 00:29:35.564
You can just drop me off
at Hyehwa station.

454
00:29:35.900 --> 00:29:36.900
Thank you.

455
00:29:36.901 --> 00:29:38.392
I don't mind if it's far away.

456
00:29:38.486 --> 00:29:42.196
- My shift is finished. anyway.
- I'll get off at Hyehwa.

457
00:29:42.657 --> 00:29:45.695
Looks like it's going to rain.

458
00:29:47.578 --> 00:29:49.911
Ride the Benz. not the subway!

459
00:29:49.998 --> 00:29:53.287
I'm meeting my boyfriend
at exit 3 of Hyehwa Station!

460
00:29:54.836 --> 00:29:55.997
Yes.

461
00:30:31.296 --> 00:30:35.336
Dad. when you worked as a driver.
did you drive a lot of Benzes?

462
00:30:36.009 --> 00:30:37.466
Benzes?

463
00:30:38.011 --> 00:30:42.221
Not then. but I did
when I worked as a valet.

464
00:30:42.808 --> 00:30:45.516
You worked as a valet?

465
00:30:45.602 --> 00:30:49.391
Sure. after the chicken place went bust.
before the Taiwan cake shop.

466
00:30:49.481 --> 00:30:51.222
in that 6-month window?

467
00:30:51.316 --> 00:30:54.684
No. it was after the cake shop
went bust.

468
00:30:57.698 --> 00:30:59.735
We're moving
to the next stage already?

469
00:31:00.409 --> 00:31:03.993
I set a trap in the Benz.

470
00:31:04.079 --> 00:31:05.866
Then we're diving right in.

471
00:31:06.165 --> 00:31:08.122
Wow. this is so metaphorical.

472
00:31:08.417 --> 00:31:12.252
Look Dad. we're eating in
a driver's cafeteria right now!

473
00:31:12.796 --> 00:31:14.583
Right. a driver's cafeteria!

474
00:31:15.048 --> 00:31:16.960
Eat as much as you want. kids.

475
00:31:17.134 --> 00:31:19.877
You didn't even pay for it.
they did!

476
00:31:20.179 --> 00:31:23.217
Son. have some more.
Eat up!

477
00:31:23.307 --> 00:31:24.265
Yes. Dad.

478
00:31:24.266 --> 00:31:25.382
Eat your fill!

479
00:31:25.475 --> 00:31:27.592
What did you do
to that woman yesterday?

480
00:31:27.686 --> 00:31:28.561
What?

481
00:31:28.562 --> 00:31:30.144
She was freaking out.

482
00:31:30.314 --> 00:31:32.306
Saying she was so moved.
you put her in shock.

483
00:31:32.733 --> 00:31:34.065
Fuck. I don't know!

484
00:31:34.151 --> 00:31:38.020
I googled 'art therapy'.
and ad-libbed the rest.

485
00:31:38.405 --> 00:31:40.522
Then suddenly she's weeping.

486
00:31:40.782 --> 00:31:43.024
Crazy bitch.
I couldn't believe it.

487
00:32:16.443 --> 00:32:18.810
Oh. you're home?

488
00:32:18.987 --> 00:32:20.478
Did you eat yet?

489
00:32:22.449 --> 00:32:23.940
Is something wrong?

490
00:32:24.034 --> 00:32:25.366
Is the housekeeper out?

491
00:32:25.452 --> 00:32:27.284
She's walking the dogs.

492
00:32:27.996 --> 00:32:29.282
Honey.

493
00:32:30.332 --> 00:32:32.415
This was under my car seat.

494
00:32:34.962 --> 00:32:37.170
Driver Yoon is such a scumbag.

495
00:32:37.256 --> 00:32:38.918
What is this?

496
00:32:39.675 --> 00:32:41.132
I'm sorry. honey.

497
00:32:41.385 --> 00:32:43.342
I didn't know
he was this kind of guy.

498
00:32:43.470 --> 00:32:46.087
Don't you pay him well?

499
00:32:46.932 --> 00:32:49.845
Is he saving up by not paying
for a motel?

500
00:32:50.185 --> 00:32:51.721
He must be a pervert.

501
00:32:51.812 --> 00:32:53.098
He likes it in the car.

502
00:32:53.188 --> 00:32:57.148
Oh. that's gross.
In his boss' car!

503
00:32:57.234 --> 00:33:01.353
A young guy's sex life is
his own business. that's all fine.

504
00:33:05.200 --> 00:33:07.817
But why in my car?

505
00:33:08.954 --> 00:33:12.914
And if so. why not in his seat?
Why cross the line like that?

506
00:33:13.000 --> 00:33:14.366
You're right.

507
00:33:14.668 --> 00:33:17.911
Does dripping his sperm
on my seat turn him on?

508
00:33:18.088 --> 00:33:20.000
I can't believe this.

509
00:33:24.636 --> 00:33:28.471
But you know
what's strangest of all?

510
00:33:29.516 --> 00:33:30.723
What?

511
00:33:31.852 --> 00:33:34.139
Usually if you have car sex.

512
00:33:34.313 --> 00:33:39.308
you might leave behind
a strand of hair. or an earring.

513
00:33:39.568 --> 00:33:40.649
Right.

514
00:33:40.819 --> 00:33:44.278
But how can you forget
your own panties?

515
00:33:44.906 --> 00:33:48.695
That's right.
It's hard to overlook.

516
00:33:50.078 --> 00:33:53.822
So it makes me quite suspicious
of this woman's condition.

517
00:33:55.167 --> 00:33:56.658
You get me?

518
00:34:06.219 --> 00:34:07.835
<i>Oh my</i>... meth or cocaine?

519
00:34:07.929 --> 00:34:09.295
Shh! The kids...

520
00:34:09.723 --> 00:34:11.214
What do we do?

521
00:34:11.475 --> 00:34:14.218
What if anyone finds white powder
in your car?

522
00:34:14.311 --> 00:34:16.473
Calm down. relax.

523
00:34:17.230 --> 00:34:18.437
Relax

524
00:34:19.191 --> 00:34:22.229
For now it's just supposition.
A rational guess.

525
00:34:23.028 --> 00:34:24.940
But no need to call the police.

526
00:34:25.030 --> 00:34:26.566
Not that!

527
00:34:27.366 --> 00:34:32.782
Still. for a busy man like me to ask.
"Why are you fucking in my car?"

528
00:34:32.871 --> 00:34:34.362
Exactly.

529
00:34:34.456 --> 00:34:36.288
So instead...

530
00:34:36.375 --> 00:34:41.086
Can you just invent some bland
excuse to let him go?

531
00:34:41.380 --> 00:34:42.791
Okay sure.

532
00:34:42.923 --> 00:34:45.961
No need to mention panties
or car sex.

533
00:34:46.426 --> 00:34:48.418
We don't need to stoop
to that level. do we?

534
00:34:48.512 --> 00:34:50.219
Surely not!

535
00:34:50.847 --> 00:34:54.011
But what if he goes online
and accuses us...

536
00:34:54.101 --> 00:34:56.184
Just give him a good severance.

537
00:34:56.478 --> 00:34:59.596
How was Da-song today?

538
00:34:59.940 --> 00:35:01.602
He was fine.

539
00:35:02.317 --> 00:35:04.650
- So class is finished?
- Yes.

540
00:35:04.736 --> 00:35:07.399
Jessica. the last time you came.

541
00:35:07.489 --> 00:35:09.902
our driver gave you a ride.
right?

542
00:35:09.991 --> 00:35:10.951
That's right.

543
00:35:10.952 --> 00:35:13.034
This may be an odd question.

544
00:35:13.328 --> 00:35:15.285
but nothing happened then?

545
00:35:15.372 --> 00:35:16.829
No. he was very nice.

546
00:35:16.915 --> 00:35:18.702
I told him
to go to Hyehwa Station.

547
00:35:18.792 --> 00:35:22.081
but he insisted
on driving me home.

548
00:35:22.170 --> 00:35:25.254
That jerk!
He took you home late at night?

549
00:35:25.340 --> 00:35:27.206
Revealing where you live?

550
00:35:27.884 --> 00:35:30.251
No. I got off at Hyehwa.

551
00:35:30.470 --> 00:35:32.678
Oh. good girl. Very good.

552
00:35:32.973 --> 00:35:34.384
Jessica nice...

553
00:35:34.516 --> 00:35:36.883
Did something happen with him?

554
00:35:37.144 --> 00:35:42.230
He won't be working for us anymore.
A slightly shameful incident.

555
00:35:42.357 --> 00:35:44.349
What incident?

556
00:35:44.443 --> 00:35:47.026
Oh. you don't need to know.

557
00:35:48.655 --> 00:35:52.524
But I'm surprised.
He was so gentlemanly and cool.

558
00:35:52.617 --> 00:35:55.985
Jessica. you're too young
and innocent!

559
00:35:56.079 --> 00:35:58.116
You have a lot to learn
about people.

560
00:35:58.832 --> 00:36:03.793
But we were excited to have such
a young. hip driver. too.

561
00:36:03.879 --> 00:36:07.043
But isn't an older driver better?

562
00:36:07.132 --> 00:36:11.001
That's true. They drive better.
have better manners.

563
00:36:11.261 --> 00:36:13.878
My father's brother had
a driver just like that.

564
00:36:13.972 --> 00:36:18.558
Mr. Kim.
He was so congenial and nice.

565
00:36:18.643 --> 00:36:21.386
I used to call him Uncle
when I was young.

566
00:36:21.771 --> 00:36:23.137
You know a man like that?

567
00:36:23.231 --> 00:36:25.939
Yes. he was so mild-mannered.

568
00:36:26.818 --> 00:36:31.358
Oh. but my relatives relocated
to Chicago.

569
00:36:32.574 --> 00:36:34.816
I wonder if Mr.
Kim's free now?

570
00:36:35.368 --> 00:36:38.907
I'm really interested!
Could I meet him?

571
00:36:38.997 --> 00:36:40.113
Really?

572
00:36:40.582 --> 00:36:42.494
I don't trust anyone now.

573
00:36:43.001 --> 00:36:45.914
I only trust someone recommended
by a person I know well.

574
00:36:46.129 --> 00:36:50.874
But if you've known him so long.
I'd feel much more at ease.

575
00:36:53.386 --> 00:36:55.002
Do you really want to meet him?

576
00:36:55.847 --> 00:36:57.554
I'm deadly serious.

577
00:36:57.766 --> 00:37:01.305
This chain of recommendations
is best.

578
00:37:01.770 --> 00:37:03.261
How should I describe it?

579
00:37:03.480 --> 00:37:04.937
A belt of trust?

580
00:37:05.106 --> 00:37:06.392
- This one's different.
- Here.

581
00:37:06.483 --> 00:37:07.149
Oh. right.

582
00:37:07.150 --> 00:37:08.516
And this one.

583
00:37:08.902 --> 00:37:10.484
Looks like a touch screen now.

584
00:37:10.570 --> 00:37:13.153
It's not touch.
it says you have to turn it.

585
00:37:13.240 --> 00:37:15.277
Wow. this thing?

586
00:37:15.951 --> 00:37:16.987
Sir?

587
00:37:17.077 --> 00:37:19.160
Taking our time. are we?

588
00:37:22.374 --> 00:37:23.831
This is a nice car.

589
00:37:26.044 --> 00:37:28.036
This is it!
Come over here.

590
00:37:31.800 --> 00:37:33.462
He's in a meeting now.

591
00:37:38.181 --> 00:37:40.047
Have a seat and wait here.

592
00:37:48.900 --> 00:37:52.268
Hello. nice to meet...

593
00:37:55.490 --> 00:37:57.026
But is it compatible
with a phone?

594
00:37:57.117 --> 00:38:03.455
Oh. not with a phone.
You need more computing power.

595
00:38:04.874 --> 00:38:09.289
This isn't any sort of test.
so don't be nervous.

596
00:38:10.130 --> 00:38:13.623
I was worn out at the office.
so I came out for a bit.

597
00:38:13.758 --> 00:38:14.965
I understand.

598
00:38:15.135 --> 00:38:19.630
Constant chatter. all that bother.
At least the car is peaceful.

599
00:38:22.100 --> 00:38:23.386
Thank you.

600
00:38:24.102 --> 00:38:25.593
You seem to know the roads well?

601
00:38:25.687 --> 00:38:28.851
Anything below the 38th parallel.

602
00:38:29.107 --> 00:38:32.441
After 30 years behind the wheel.
the car almost drives itself.

603
00:38:32.652 --> 00:38:35.395
I respect those who work
in one field for a long time.

604
00:38:35.780 --> 00:38:38.488
Well. to be honest.
this is a simple vocation.

605
00:38:38.575 --> 00:38:41.693
But... the head of a household.

606
00:38:41.995 --> 00:38:44.032
the leader of a company?

607
00:38:44.164 --> 00:38:48.909
Or else just a lonely man setting off
on the road each morning...

608
00:38:49.628 --> 00:38:51.665
It's companionship of a sort.

609
00:38:52.005 --> 00:38:54.839
so that's how I've approached each day.

610
00:38:54.966 --> 00:38:57.174
The years sure pass quickly.

611
00:39:00.639 --> 00:39:03.131
Sure enough.
your cornering is excellent.

612
00:39:04.059 --> 00:39:09.930
Well. it may look simple.
but it's one of the fundamentals.

613
00:39:10.357 --> 00:39:14.897
<i>She may look like a sheep.
but inside. she's a fox.</i>

614
00:39:15.320 --> 00:39:18.188
<i>Sometimes she acts like
she owns the house.</i>

615
00:39:18.823 --> 00:39:19.823
<i>Right.</i>

616
00:39:19.866 --> 00:39:24.281
<i>Of all the people in that house.
she's lived there the longest.</i>

617
00:39:24.496 --> 00:39:27.989
<i>She was housekeeper
to the architect Namgoong.</i>

618
00:39:28.208 --> 00:39:32.498
<i>but then she went on to work
for this family.</i>

619
00:39:32.962 --> 00:39:34.749
<i>When the architect moved out.</i>

620
00:39:34.839 --> 00:39:37.707
<i>he introduced this woman
to Park's family.</i>

621
00:39:37.842 --> 00:39:41.176
<i>telling them. "This is a great housekeeper.
you should hire her."</i>

622
00:39:41.262 --> 00:39:44.596
<i>So she survived
a change of ownership.</i>

623
00:39:44.683 --> 00:39:47.676
She won't give up
a good job easily.

624
00:39:47.936 --> 00:39:51.475
To extract a woman like that.
we need to prepare well.

625
00:39:52.816 --> 00:39:55.399
Right. we need a plan.

626
00:39:56.569 --> 00:39:59.812
I want to eat peaches.
I like peaches best.

627
00:40:00.407 --> 00:40:01.818
Why not ask for some?

628
00:40:01.908 --> 00:40:05.401
No peaches at our house.
It's forbidden fruit.

629
00:40:13.211 --> 00:40:16.170
<i>So according to
what Da-hye told me.</i>

630
00:40:16.339 --> 00:40:20.583
<i>she's got a massively serious
allergy to peaches.</i>

631
00:40:20.927 --> 00:40:24.045
<i>You know that fuzz
on a peach's skin?</i>

632
00:40:24.305 --> 00:40:28.015
<i>If she's anywhere near it.
she gets a full body rash.</i>

633
00:40:28.101 --> 00:40:31.845
<i>has trouble breathing. asthma.
a total meltdown!</i>

634
00:40:36.526 --> 00:40:40.440
No no. there weren't
any peaches anywhere.

635
00:40:42.540 --> 00:40:44.873
That's what I'm saying!

636
00:40:45.168 --> 00:40:47.706
Usually when I get symptoms
like this.

637
00:40:48.004 --> 00:40:51.088
I run to my room
and take my medicine.

638
00:40:51.299 --> 00:40:56.761
but it was so sudden.
I wasn't sure where I left it.

639
00:40:56.929 --> 00:41:01.720
Madame. this woman behind me.
is that...?

640
00:41:01.976 --> 00:41:03.808
Oh. it's our housekeeper!

641
00:41:03.895 --> 00:41:06.228
So it's true. Oh. how sad.

642
00:41:06.731 --> 00:41:09.439
I wasn't sure
if that was really her.

643
00:41:09.817 --> 00:41:13.527
I've only seen her a couple times
in the living room.

644
00:41:14.113 --> 00:41:16.070
This was in the hospital?

645
00:41:16.157 --> 00:41:19.946
A few days ago I went
for my annual medical exam.

646
00:41:20.453 --> 00:41:24.663
I took a selfie for my wife.
and there she was behind me.

647
00:41:25.083 --> 00:41:27.291
Is she talking
on the phone there?

648
00:41:27.376 --> 00:41:30.460
Anyway. I wasn't trying
to eavesdrop...

649
00:41:30.546 --> 00:41:32.412
I wasn't trying
to eavesdrop.

650
00:41:32.507 --> 00:41:34.339
but her words
came through clearly!

651
00:41:34.425 --> 00:41:36.212
- So I couldn't help but...!
- Cut. cut!

652
00:41:36.302 --> 00:41:39.261
Dad. your emotions are up
to here.

653
00:41:39.347 --> 00:41:41.589
Bring them down to
about there.

654
00:41:41.891 --> 00:41:44.599
...so I couldn't help
but overhear.

655
00:41:44.685 --> 00:41:46.972
Keep it focused!

656
00:41:48.606 --> 00:41:51.223
What I'm trying to say is.
it's just that.

657
00:41:51.317 --> 00:41:55.357
your housekeeper's voice
is quite loud. you know?

658
00:41:55.738 --> 00:41:59.231
I understand. it's all right.
Just tell me. okay?

659
00:41:59.325 --> 00:42:02.193
She said she got diagnosed
with active TB.

660
00:42:02.286 --> 00:42:04.243
and she was shouting
on the phone.

661
00:42:04.330 --> 00:42:07.414
so upset she could
barely control herself!

662
00:42:07.500 --> 00:42:09.867
Tuberculosis?
Come on...

663
00:42:09.961 --> 00:42:15.127
It's true. she phoned someone
saying she had active TB.

664
00:42:15.591 --> 00:42:20.177
Do people still get TB?

665
00:42:20.680 --> 00:42:21.680
Dad...

666
00:42:21.806 --> 00:42:26.892
Back in the day. people used
to buy Christmas Seals. right?

667
00:42:27.103 --> 00:42:28.435
Feels like a bygone era.

668
00:42:28.521 --> 00:42:29.978
But I saw it on the internet.

669
00:42:30.189 --> 00:42:34.024
Korea has the #1 rate of TB
of all the OECD countries.

670
00:42:34.110 --> 00:42:37.729
But she's still working.
as if nothing's wrong.

671
00:42:37.822 --> 00:42:39.734
With a kid like Da-song
in the house.

672
00:42:39.824 --> 00:42:42.908
So you've got a young kid
like Da-song in the house.

673
00:42:43.202 --> 00:42:46.320
and a TB patient is doing dishes.
cooking. spraying spittle...

674
00:42:46.414 --> 00:42:47.700
Stop it. please!

675
00:42:52.253 --> 00:42:53.994
<i>Dad: Arriving in 3 mins</i>

676
00:43:40.885 --> 00:43:44.674
If you get the chance.
this'll be icing on the cake.

677
00:44:14.961 --> 00:44:16.668
<i>Madame</i>

678
00:44:16.754 --> 00:44:18.541
<i>2nd floor sauna room</i>

679
00:44:18.631 --> 00:44:19.838
<i>Don't let her see you</i>

680
00:44:30.268 --> 00:44:32.009
- Have a seat.
- Yes.

681
00:44:33.980 --> 00:44:35.016
Mr. Kim.

682
00:44:35.106 --> 00:44:39.066
Please don't tell any of this
to my husband. okay?

683
00:44:39.277 --> 00:44:40.313
Understood.

684
00:44:40.903 --> 00:44:45.273
If he hears I brought
a TB patient to our home.

685
00:44:45.741 --> 00:44:48.484
I'll be hanged and quartered!

686
00:44:48.577 --> 00:44:50.159
Don't worry. Madame.

687
00:44:50.537 --> 00:44:53.951
And if I may presume
to say one thing.

688
00:44:54.249 --> 00:44:57.413
I have no feelings
against that woman.

689
00:44:57.961 --> 00:45:04.961
I felt I had to speak up for the sake
of public health and hygiene.

690
00:45:05.594 --> 00:45:09.133
But this could be
seen as snitching or...

691
00:45:09.223 --> 00:45:10.589
Don't you worry.

692
00:45:10.682 --> 00:45:13.265
I won't mention the TB.

693
00:45:13.352 --> 00:45:15.765
I'll just make up some excuse
to dismiss her.

694
00:45:15.896 --> 00:45:17.637
Simply and quietly.

695
00:45:19.066 --> 00:45:21.729
It's a proven method.
That's the best.

696
00:45:21.819 --> 00:45:23.401
Okay. then.

697
00:45:34.623 --> 00:45:37.491
Have you... washed your hands?

698
00:46:23.255 --> 00:46:27.465
Mr. Kim. do you know
a good braised ribs place?

699
00:46:27.551 --> 00:46:29.087
Somewhere close by.

700
00:46:29.303 --> 00:46:30.544
Sure.

701
00:46:30.679 --> 00:46:34.468
- Then you'll be eating out?
- That's right.

702
00:46:35.100 --> 00:46:37.843
Why such a craving
for braised ribs today?

703
00:46:38.312 --> 00:46:41.305
Our old housekeeper made delicious ribs.

704
00:46:42.232 --> 00:46:45.066
The one who quit this week?

705
00:46:46.028 --> 00:46:49.487
My wife wouldn't even tell me
why she quit.

706
00:46:52.284 --> 00:46:57.245
Sure. it's easy enough
to hire a new one.

707
00:46:58.498 --> 00:47:03.243
Still. it's a shame.
She was a great housekeeper.

708
00:47:03.337 --> 00:47:04.337
I see.

709
00:47:04.379 --> 00:47:06.962
She kept the house
in great shape.

710
00:47:07.049 --> 00:47:09.666
and she knew never
to cross the line.

711
00:47:10.260 --> 00:47:12.923
I can't stand people
who cross the line.

712
00:47:13.513 --> 00:47:16.176
Perhaps just one weak point?

713
00:47:17.092 --> 00:47:18.674
Eating too much.

714
00:47:18.802 --> 00:47:21.294
She always ate enough for two.

715
00:47:22.347 --> 00:47:26.136
But considering all the work
she did...

716
00:47:26.309 --> 00:47:31.600
Then you better find someone new.
A new housekeeper.

717
00:47:31.773 --> 00:47:33.730
We're in trouble now.

718
00:47:33.859 --> 00:47:38.229
In a week. our house will be
a trash can.

719
00:47:39.114 --> 00:47:41.857
My clothes will start
to smell.

720
00:47:43.326 --> 00:47:46.160
My wife has no talent for housework.

721
00:47:46.371 --> 00:47:49.580
She's bad at cleaning.
and her cooking's awful.

722
00:47:50.500 --> 00:47:52.617
Still. you love her. right?

723
00:48:00.302 --> 00:48:03.386
Of course. I love her.

724
00:48:04.431 --> 00:48:06.343
We'll call it love.

725
00:48:08.143 --> 00:48:10.055
Then would this help?

726
00:48:14.107 --> 00:48:16.474
The Care?
What is this?

727
00:48:16.651 --> 00:48:19.018
I just recently found out
about them.

728
00:48:19.279 --> 00:48:23.819
How to describe it?
It's like a membership service.

729
00:48:24.659 --> 00:48:31.031
The company provides veteran-grade
help to VIP customers such as you.

730
00:48:31.208 --> 00:48:37.205
For example maids. caregivers.
or drivers like myself.

731
00:48:37.297 --> 00:48:40.256
You can tell from the card
they're high-class.

732
00:48:40.842 --> 00:48:42.458
Cool design.

733
00:48:43.720 --> 00:48:45.677
Then how do you know
about this company?

734
00:48:45.764 --> 00:48:50.099
They contacted me.
as a veteran-grade driver.

735
00:48:50.352 --> 00:48:52.594
You might say they scouted me?

736
00:48:53.813 --> 00:49:00.105
But when their call came I had
already arranged to meet with you.

737
00:49:01.529 --> 00:49:02.895
I see...

738
00:49:04.032 --> 00:49:07.275
You turned down this famous company
to work for me.

739
00:49:07.869 --> 00:49:09.531
I won't forget that.

740
00:49:10.580 --> 00:49:12.947
Son of a bitch!

741
00:49:14.960 --> 00:49:19.000
Anyway. I can give this card
to my wife. right?

742
00:49:19.214 --> 00:49:20.921
Yes. that's why I brought it up.

743
00:49:21.007 --> 00:49:22.999
No need to mention me.

744
00:49:24.261 --> 00:49:27.675
You can tell her
you found the company yourself.

745
00:49:28.265 --> 00:49:29.506
Sure.

746
00:49:29.849 --> 00:49:32.182
Thanks to you I can play
the good husband.

747
00:49:32.269 --> 00:49:36.934
On the back. there's a number
for consultations.

748
00:49:37.148 --> 00:49:38.264
Tell her to call there...

749
00:49:38.358 --> 00:49:39.644
Eyes on the road!

750
00:49:44.781 --> 00:49:48.024
Hello. this is
Senior Advisor Yeo of The Care.

751
00:49:48.326 --> 00:49:51.410
Yes. this is The Care's main office?

752
00:49:51.579 --> 00:49:52.579
That's correct.

753
00:49:52.580 --> 00:49:56.039
If she wanted. she'd be
a fucking great con artist.

754
00:49:56.126 --> 00:49:58.493
Isn't her voice tone great?
Takes after me.

755
00:50:00.088 --> 00:50:02.705
From what I've heard.
it's a full membership service?

756
00:50:02.882 --> 00:50:06.717
So you're not currently
a member. I assume?

757
00:50:06.803 --> 00:50:09.386
<i>That's right. What steps do
I need to take?</i>

758
00:50:09.472 --> 00:50:13.591
We'll just need to receive
a few documents from you.

759
00:50:13.685 --> 00:50:16.598
Are you ready
to write this down?

760
00:50:16.771 --> 00:50:21.391
Your family register.
citizenship ID cards...

761
00:50:22.402 --> 00:50:25.236
...documents to prove
your income level.

762
00:50:25.447 --> 00:50:27.814
i.e. the title to your property. etc.

763
00:50:27.907 --> 00:50:30.149
Our property title?
Yes.

764
00:50:38.668 --> 00:50:40.204
Wow. peaches!

765
00:50:40.337 --> 00:50:42.078
You have some too. Mr. Kevin.

766
00:50:42.547 --> 00:50:43.788
Thank you.

767
00:50:52.390 --> 00:50:54.632
Leave it outside
the door next time.

768
00:50:54.726 --> 00:50:57.389
- And knock!
- Yes.

769
00:51:00.231 --> 00:51:01.813
No entering during my lesson!

770
00:51:01.900 --> 00:51:02.981
Yes. miss!

771
00:51:05.528 --> 00:51:06.860
<i>Park Da-song!</i>

772
00:51:06.946 --> 00:51:08.107
Daddy!

773
00:51:08.198 --> 00:51:09.655
<i>Where are you?</i>

774
00:51:14.120 --> 00:51:15.281
Daddy!

775
00:51:15.372 --> 00:51:16.330
Son!

776
00:51:16.331 --> 00:51:17.947
Walkie talkies!

777
00:51:18.041 --> 00:51:19.041
Walkie talkies?

778
00:51:19.125 --> 00:51:20.125
Walkie talkies!

779
00:51:20.210 --> 00:51:23.419
Who do you like better.
your dad or the walkie talkie?

780
00:51:24.172 --> 00:51:26.710
Da-song. how could you run out
from your lesson?

781
00:51:27.092 --> 00:51:30.631
When did you buy all this?

782
00:51:30.762 --> 00:51:31.798
It's no big deal.

783
00:51:31.888 --> 00:51:32.969
Huh?

784
00:51:36.101 --> 00:51:37.137
Huh?

785
00:51:37.685 --> 00:51:38.801
What is it?

786
00:51:41.731 --> 00:51:42.847
What's he doing now?

787
00:51:44.401 --> 00:51:45.482
Da-song. don't do that!

788
00:51:45.527 --> 00:51:49.271
It's the same!
They smell the same!

789
00:51:49.489 --> 00:51:52.778
What are you talking about?
Go up to Jessica.

790
00:51:53.159 --> 00:51:56.903
Jessica smells like that. too.

791
00:51:57.997 --> 00:52:01.616
So do we all need
to use different soap. now?

792
00:52:01.709 --> 00:52:05.578
Dad. we'll need to use
different laundry soap. too.

793
00:52:05.672 --> 00:52:06.833
And fabric softener.

794
00:52:06.923 --> 00:52:11.042
You mean doing four separate loads
of laundry each time?

795
00:52:11.219 --> 00:52:12.960
That's not it.

796
00:52:13.930 --> 00:52:16.013
It's the semi-basement smell.

797
00:52:16.975 --> 00:52:19.683
We need to leave this home
to lose the smell.

798
00:52:21.688 --> 00:52:27.434
Anyway. aren't we fortunate to be
worrying about things like this?

799
00:52:27.527 --> 00:52:28.563
Sure.

800
00:52:28.653 --> 00:52:31.521
In an age like ours.

801
00:52:31.948 --> 00:52:36.443
when an opening for a security guard
attracts 500 university graduates.

802
00:52:36.661 --> 00:52:39.825
Our entire family got hired!

803
00:52:40.415 --> 00:52:42.031
That's right. Dad!

804
00:52:42.542 --> 00:52:45.000
If we put our 4 salaries together?

805
00:52:45.211 --> 00:52:49.251
The amount of cash coming
from that house into ours is immense!

806
00:52:50.175 --> 00:52:54.715
Let's offer a prayer of gratitude
to the great Mr. Park.

807
00:52:54.804 --> 00:52:55.885
And to Min!

808
00:52:55.972 --> 00:52:58.715
Ki-woo. that friend of yours
turned into such a fine guy.

809
00:52:58.808 --> 00:53:03.052
and thanks to him we're all...
Fuck. not again!

810
00:53:07.775 --> 00:53:08.775
That asshole's dead.

811
00:53:08.860 --> 00:53:11.352
Ki-woo's on the rampage!

812
00:53:11.446 --> 00:53:13.608
Don't overdo it!

813
00:53:14.824 --> 00:53:17.362
Use this instead.

814
00:53:21.122 --> 00:53:22.363
Damn you!

815
00:53:25.168 --> 00:53:26.454
Get a fucking grip!

816
00:53:26.544 --> 00:53:28.035
Get a grip!

817
00:53:30.548 --> 00:53:31.914
Wow!

818
00:53:36.221 --> 00:53:38.429
It's a deluge!

819
00:53:54.697 --> 00:53:59.032
Current weather is clear. over.
The clouds are moving.

820
00:53:59.118 --> 00:54:01.531
<i>But they're not rain clouds.
over.</i>

821
00:54:01.621 --> 00:54:03.032
I hear you. over.

822
00:54:03.122 --> 00:54:09.289
Currently your sister's lip is
pouting like a duck's bill.

823
00:54:09.504 --> 00:54:12.247
She's super annoyed. over.

824
00:54:12.590 --> 00:54:17.176
Can't I stay home and study English?
And call Kevin?

825
00:54:17.387 --> 00:54:20.801
Hey! Don't make a scene
just as we're leaving.

826
00:54:20.890 --> 00:54:23.223
If we have to go.
let's have fun.

827
00:54:23.309 --> 00:54:25.972
Da-hye. this is no ordinary
camping trip.

828
00:54:26.062 --> 00:54:26.895
That's right!

829
00:54:26.896 --> 00:54:29.013
How could you miss
your brother's birthday?

830
00:54:29.107 --> 00:54:29.856
No way!

831
00:54:29.857 --> 00:54:32.099
Even your busy father is
taking time off to go.

832
00:54:32.193 --> 00:54:34.981
Right! If you don't go.
you'll regret it!

833
00:54:37.365 --> 00:54:39.527
Oh. right.
You know the beam projector?

834
00:54:39.617 --> 00:54:40.617
The outdoor theater?

835
00:54:40.702 --> 00:54:42.568
Right. bring the outdoor
beam projector.

836
00:54:42.662 --> 00:54:43.454
Yes.

837
00:54:43.455 --> 00:54:47.573
And look for Da-song's
camping raincoat.

838
00:54:47.750 --> 00:54:49.457
He loves it when it rains.

839
00:54:50.086 --> 00:54:54.046
You remember now?
Zoonie. Berry. and Foofoo.

840
00:54:54.132 --> 00:54:55.293
Zoonie and Berry get this.

841
00:54:55.383 --> 00:54:58.171
Yes. Natural Balance Original Ultra.

842
00:54:58.261 --> 00:55:00.548
Right. and for Foofoo...

843
00:55:00.930 --> 00:55:02.546
Kani-kamaboko.
Japanese crab sticks.

844
00:55:02.640 --> 00:55:03.640
Yes.

845
00:55:03.641 --> 00:55:06.679
When you walk Zoonie.
give him a long leash.

846
00:55:06.769 --> 00:55:09.557
He needs to run around
to feel happy.

847
00:55:09.647 --> 00:55:12.264
He's like the canine version
of Da-song!

848
00:55:38.092 --> 00:55:39.583
Son!

849
00:55:40.053 --> 00:55:42.796
Why are you lying down outside?

850
00:55:43.056 --> 00:55:45.639
Isn't he hot out there?

851
00:55:46.601 --> 00:55:51.221
I'm gazing at the sky
from home.

852
00:55:52.857 --> 00:55:54.314
It's so great.

853
00:55:57.737 --> 00:55:59.899
Mom. want some water?

854
00:55:59.989 --> 00:56:01.196
There's sparkling. right?

855
00:56:01.491 --> 00:56:03.983
Ki-jung. some water?

856
00:56:04.077 --> 00:56:06.069
Telepathy... thank you.

857
00:56:28.393 --> 00:56:29.634
Whoa.

858
00:56:32.397 --> 00:56:35.060
Wow. all these varieties
of alcohol.

859
00:56:36.025 --> 00:56:40.269
Dad! Let me add another
to the mix!

860
00:56:42.156 --> 00:56:43.818
This is pretty classy.

861
00:56:44.742 --> 00:56:49.407
Rain falling on the lawn.
as we sip our whiskey...

862
00:56:49.997 --> 00:56:54.742
Ki-woo. what's that yellow notebook
you've been carrying?

863
00:56:55.420 --> 00:56:58.834
This?
It's Da-hye's diary.

864
00:56:58.923 --> 00:57:00.459
Her diary?

865
00:57:00.550 --> 00:57:04.669
What a scumbag.
How could you read her diary?

866
00:57:05.263 --> 00:57:10.634
Just so we can understand
each other deeper.

867
00:57:10.727 --> 00:57:13.185
Fuck. are you two dating?

868
00:57:13.646 --> 00:57:17.640
I'm serious.
She really likes me too.

869
00:57:19.777 --> 00:57:21.234
A while back...

870
00:57:22.113 --> 00:57:23.320
Never mind.

871
00:57:24.407 --> 00:57:27.366
When she enters university.
I'll officially ask her out.

872
00:57:27.702 --> 00:57:28.988
Seriously.

873
00:57:33.666 --> 00:57:35.373
My son!

874
00:57:35.877 --> 00:57:40.212
Then this house will be
your in-laws' house?

875
00:57:42.717 --> 00:57:43.798
That's right.

876
00:57:43.885 --> 00:57:47.845
Fuck. then I'm washing dishes
at my daughter-in-law's?

877
00:57:47.930 --> 00:57:51.173
Sure. washing
your daughter-in-law's socks!

878
00:58:03.070 --> 00:58:08.156
I like her.
She's a good kid.

879
00:58:08.659 --> 00:58:12.653
She's pretty.
but she's not wild.

880
00:58:13.706 --> 00:58:17.950
Well. now that we're daydreaming...

881
00:58:19.212 --> 00:58:21.750
If Da-hye and I marry.

882
00:58:21.964 --> 00:58:25.674
we can bring in actors
to be my mom and dad.

883
00:58:26.594 --> 00:58:27.755
Look at her.

884
00:58:27.887 --> 00:58:31.380
She got so many jobs acting
in weddings last year.

885
00:58:32.892 --> 00:58:35.976
I even caught the bouquet
from a bitch I've never met.

886
00:58:36.229 --> 00:58:39.188
If you get the bouquet.
they pay an extra $10.

887
00:58:39.315 --> 00:58:41.432
That's how your acting got so good!

888
00:58:41.526 --> 00:58:46.897
Acting is one thing.
but this family is so gullible. right?

889
00:58:46.989 --> 00:58:49.197
The madame especially.

890
00:58:49.283 --> 00:58:50.899
You said it.

891
00:58:52.829 --> 00:58:56.038
She's so naive. and nice.

892
00:58:56.374 --> 00:58:58.457
She's rich. but still nice.

893
00:58:58.543 --> 00:59:00.751
Not "rich. but still nice."

894
00:59:00.920 --> 00:59:04.584
"Nice because she's rich."
You know?

895
00:59:05.091 --> 00:59:11.588
Hell. if I had all this money.

896
00:59:12.807 --> 00:59:16.551
I'd be nice too!

897
00:59:17.019 --> 00:59:18.430
Even nicer!

898
00:59:18.771 --> 00:59:20.808
That's true.
Your mom's right.

899
00:59:21.148 --> 00:59:23.390
Rich people are naive.
No resentments.

900
00:59:23.609 --> 00:59:25.942
No creases on them.

901
00:59:26.028 --> 00:59:29.112
It all gets ironed out.
Money is an iron.

902
00:59:29.365 --> 00:59:31.857
Those creases all get smoothed out.

903
00:59:31.993 --> 00:59:33.234
Hey. Ki-woo.

904
00:59:34.678 --> 00:59:39.343
You know that driver. Yoon?
Was it Yoon?

905
00:59:40.017 --> 00:59:42.304
The driver before me.

906
00:59:42.644 --> 00:59:43.805
Yeah. Yoon.

907
00:59:43.896 --> 00:59:48.482
He must be working somewhere else now.
right?

908
00:59:48.567 --> 00:59:50.900
Sure. he must be.

909
00:59:50.986 --> 00:59:54.229
He's young. got a nice physique.

910
00:59:54.823 --> 00:59:57.691
He must've found a better job.

911
00:59:57.784 --> 01:00:00.026
Fucking hell!

912
01:00:00.871 --> 01:00:03.033
What's with her now?

913
01:00:03.540 --> 01:00:09.537
We're the ones who need help.
Worry about us. okay?

914
01:00:10.047 --> 01:00:13.256
Dad! Come on. Dad!

915
01:00:13.550 --> 01:00:17.794
Just focus on us. okay?
On us!

916
01:00:18.013 --> 01:00:22.348
Not Driver Yoon. but me. please!

917
01:00:22.476 --> 01:00:24.559
Awesome timing. huh?

918
01:00:24.686 --> 01:00:28.430
She speaks.
and the lightning crashes!

919
01:00:30.526 --> 01:00:33.360
Hey. Jessica. Cheers.

920
01:00:34.238 --> 01:00:40.030
Hey. when I went up before.
and you were in the bath...

921
01:00:40.118 --> 01:00:41.700
What about it?

922
01:00:42.579 --> 01:00:45.743
How to put it?
You fit in here.

923
01:00:46.083 --> 01:00:48.996
This rich house suits you.
Not like us.

924
01:00:49.086 --> 01:00:50.002
Fuck off.

925
01:00:50.003 --> 01:00:50.921
I'm serious!

926
01:00:50.922 --> 01:00:52.662
Dad. before...

927
01:00:52.756 --> 01:00:55.419
She was lying back in the tub.
watching TV.

928
01:00:55.968 --> 01:00:58.301
Like she's lived here for years.

929
01:01:00.264 --> 01:01:06.101
Speaking of which.
if this became our house.

930
01:01:06.228 --> 01:01:10.347
if we lived here.
which room would you want?

931
01:01:10.566 --> 01:01:15.652
What room in this masterwork
by the great Namgoong?

932
01:01:15.862 --> 01:01:17.774
Fuck. I don't know.

933
01:01:17.864 --> 01:01:21.528
Get me the house first.
Then I'll think about it.

934
01:01:21.868 --> 01:01:24.110
We live here now. don't we?

935
01:01:24.580 --> 01:01:28.369
Getting drunk in the living room.

936
01:01:28.500 --> 01:01:31.538
Right. we live here.
Why not?

937
01:01:31.670 --> 01:01:36.085
This is our home right now.
It's cosy.

938
01:01:36.300 --> 01:01:39.213
Cosy? Are you feeling cosy?

939
01:01:39.428 --> 01:01:44.298
Sure. but suppose Park walked
through that door now.

940
01:01:44.891 --> 01:01:46.302
What about your dad?

941
01:01:46.435 --> 01:01:49.769
He'd run and hide like a cockroach.

942
01:01:50.272 --> 01:01:52.764
Kids. you know at our house.

943
01:01:52.858 --> 01:01:58.445
when you turn on the light.
and the cockroaches scatter?

944
01:01:58.655 --> 01:02:00.396
You know what I mean?

945
01:02:01.033 --> 01:02:04.151
I'm getting fucking tired of this.

946
01:02:04.911 --> 01:02:06.743
- A cockroach?
- Yeah.

947
01:02:10.500 --> 01:02:12.162
Huh? What's wrong?

948
01:02:12.252 --> 01:02:13.584
What's the matter?

949
01:02:13.670 --> 01:02:17.254
Dad. don't do that.
You only live once.

950
01:02:24.556 --> 01:02:26.263
What the hell?

951
01:02:26.516 --> 01:02:28.052
I fooled you!
Didn't I?

952
01:02:28.143 --> 01:02:29.509
Jesus. Dad.

953
01:02:29.603 --> 01:02:33.768
I fooled you too. Ki-woo?
Did it look for real?

954
01:02:33.857 --> 01:02:37.271
If it was for real.
I'd fucking kill you.

955
01:02:37.653 --> 01:02:41.272
What is this?
Fucking puppy.

956
01:02:47.037 --> 01:02:49.120
Who is it at this hour?

957
01:02:49.414 --> 01:02:50.996
What is it?

958
01:02:57.547 --> 01:02:58.879
What's she doing here?

959
01:02:59.091 --> 01:03:01.378
The old housekeeper?

960
01:03:02.094 --> 01:03:03.756
What's she here for?

961
01:03:04.304 --> 01:03:08.423
She won't stop ringing it.

962
01:03:09.309 --> 01:03:12.143
Raising a racket.

963
01:03:13.605 --> 01:03:14.605
Who is it?

964
01:03:14.606 --> 01:03:19.101
Oh. hello! I'm...

965
01:03:19.486 --> 01:03:21.148
The madame's not in. right?

966
01:03:21.238 --> 01:03:22.238
What?

967
01:03:22.239 --> 01:03:26.609
I worked here
for a very long time.

968
01:03:27.160 --> 01:03:32.906
Above the monitor there.
you see a photo of 3 dogs. right?

969
01:03:32.999 --> 01:03:34.410
Zoonie. Berry. Foofoo.

970
01:03:34.501 --> 01:03:38.791
I get it.
but why are you here?

971
01:03:39.047 --> 01:03:43.508
You're my successor
as housekeeper. right?

972
01:03:48.640 --> 01:03:50.176
Anyway...

973
01:03:51.143 --> 01:03:54.261
I'm very sorry
to call on you so late.

974
01:03:54.521 --> 01:03:55.978
It's just that...

975
01:03:56.565 --> 01:04:03.565
I forgot something in the basement
under the kitchen.

976
01:04:04.114 --> 01:04:10.202
When I left. they pushed me out
so quickly...

977
01:04:13.707 --> 01:04:15.539
Would you let me in?

978
01:04:17.836 --> 01:04:19.498
What do we do?

979
01:04:20.338 --> 01:04:22.421
This isn't in the plan.

980
01:04:30.182 --> 01:04:31.969
Sorry for the trouble.

981
01:04:32.517 --> 01:04:33.553
This way.

982
01:04:33.643 --> 01:04:34.679
Yes. thank you.

983
01:04:37.063 --> 01:04:39.271
You can put your raincoat...

984
01:04:39.357 --> 01:04:41.519
It'll just be a second.

985
01:04:42.527 --> 01:04:46.020
Quite a meal there.
That'll be a job to clean up.

986
01:04:46.198 --> 01:04:49.282
But what did you leave below?

987
01:04:53.997 --> 01:04:56.239
Want to come down with me?

988
01:04:57.709 --> 01:05:00.747
Well. just go ahead.

989
01:05:54.057 --> 01:05:57.141
Help me push this!

990
01:05:57.686 --> 01:06:00.178
Pull it! From over there.

991
01:06:00.272 --> 01:06:01.513
What?

992
01:06:01.773 --> 01:06:02.934
Pull!

993
01:06:05.360 --> 01:06:06.976
Pull it hard!

994
01:06:10.907 --> 01:06:12.318
Are you okay?

995
01:06:13.618 --> 01:06:15.200
Did I scare you?

996
01:06:17.497 --> 01:06:18.954
Thank you!

997
01:06:20.333 --> 01:06:21.665
Thank you.

998
01:06:29.843 --> 01:06:30.843
Honey!

999
01:06:30.886 --> 01:06:32.343
What the hell?

1000
01:06:33.388 --> 01:06:34.469
Hey!

1001
01:06:34.556 --> 01:06:35.888
Honey!

1002
01:06:37.100 --> 01:06:38.432
Honey!

1003
01:06:41.104 --> 01:06:42.140
Wait!

1004
01:06:42.272 --> 01:06:44.389
Honey. I'm here!

1005
01:06:44.608 --> 01:06:46.099
What is all this?

1006
01:06:48.320 --> 01:06:49.401
Honey!

1007
01:06:49.938 --> 01:06:51.600
Honey. I'm fine.

1008
01:06:51.689 --> 01:06:53.396
No you're not!

1009
01:06:53.691 --> 01:06:54.772
I'm fine. really.

1010
01:06:54.859 --> 01:06:56.020
How can you say that?

1011
01:06:56.111 --> 01:06:57.852
But I'm really hungry.

1012
01:06:57.946 --> 01:06:58.946
Suck it!

1013
01:06:58.988 --> 01:07:01.981
How many days has it been?

1014
01:07:02.242 --> 01:07:03.949
You must've been so hungry!

1015
01:07:05.995 --> 01:07:07.281
It's okay.

1016
01:07:07.372 --> 01:07:10.115
She's a nice woman. She let me in.

1017
01:07:10.208 --> 01:07:12.245
There was an iron plate.
for grilling meat.

1018
01:07:12.335 --> 01:07:13.871
It was wedged under the shelf.

1019
01:07:13.962 --> 01:07:14.998
So that's why.

1020
01:07:15.088 --> 01:07:18.422
I couldn't open it
from the inside.

1021
01:07:18.675 --> 01:07:21.713
- What's going on here?
- I know you must be startled.

1022
01:07:22.262 --> 01:07:24.629
I would be too in this situation.

1023
01:07:24.806 --> 01:07:29.551
But as two fellow workers...
Right. Chung-sook?

1024
01:07:31.000 --> 01:07:32.900
How do you know my name?

1025
01:07:32.939 --> 01:07:37.559
To be honest I'm still texting
with the boy Da-song.

1026
01:07:37.777 --> 01:07:42.317
I knew they were going camping.
so I came today.

1027
01:07:42.448 --> 01:07:45.065
I wanted to speak to you alone.

1028
01:07:45.326 --> 01:07:46.692
<i>Talking about.</i>

1029
01:07:48.830 --> 01:07:51.243
Don't worry. Chung-sook.

1030
01:07:51.416 --> 01:07:54.830
I cut the wire
on the CCTV by the gate.

1031
01:07:55.211 --> 01:07:58.921
Nobody knows I came.
Isn't that good. sis?

1032
01:07:59.007 --> 01:08:01.044
Don't call me sis!

1033
01:08:01.134 --> 01:08:04.047
Sis. my name is Moon-gwang.

1034
01:08:04.304 --> 01:08:08.674
This is my hubbie Oh Geun-sae.
Say hello. honey.

1035
01:08:08.766 --> 01:08:12.134
This tastes great.
What happened to your face?

1036
01:08:12.228 --> 01:08:15.517
I'll tell you later.

1037
01:08:15.607 --> 01:08:19.567
So you'd steal food every day
while working in the kitchen.

1038
01:08:19.652 --> 01:08:20.893
Feeding your husband.

1039
01:08:20.987 --> 01:08:25.322
Not at all! I bought all his food
with my salary.

1040
01:08:25.450 --> 01:08:28.488
That's so unfair!

1041
01:08:28.703 --> 01:08:31.241
But how long has
your husband been down here?

1042
01:08:31.331 --> 01:08:33.789
Hold on a sec.
4 years?

1043
01:08:34.709 --> 01:08:37.452
4 years. 3 months and 17 days.

1044
01:08:37.545 --> 01:08:39.377
Right. it's June now.

1045
01:08:39.839 --> 01:08:45.710
Four years ago
when Mr. Namgoong moved to Paris.

1046
01:08:46.012 --> 01:08:48.675
in the time before Mr. Park's family
moved in.

1047
01:08:49.224 --> 01:08:52.717
I brought my husband down here.

1048
01:08:52.810 --> 01:08:57.646
Many rich houses have secret bunkers.
where you can hide

1049
01:08:57.815 --> 01:09:02.435
in case North Korea attacks.
or if creditors break in.

1050
01:09:02.570 --> 01:09:08.532
But it seems Mr. Namgoong was
a bit embarrassed about this.

1051
01:09:08.743 --> 01:09:12.487
because he never mentioned it
to Mr. Park's family.

1052
01:09:12.664 --> 01:09:14.121
So only I know about it.

1053
01:09:14.207 --> 01:09:16.494
So that's how it happened.

1054
01:09:16.793 --> 01:09:21.003
But now that I know. I've no choice
but to call the police!

1055
01:09:21.089 --> 01:09:22.921
No please. sis!

1056
01:09:23.299 --> 01:09:26.337
As fellow members of the needy.
please don't.

1057
01:09:26.427 --> 01:09:27.918
I'm not needy!

1058
01:09:28.012 --> 01:09:31.722
But we're needy!

1059
01:09:31.808 --> 01:09:36.052
We've no house. no money.
only debts!

1060
01:09:36.312 --> 01:09:37.553
Sis. please!

1061
01:09:37.647 --> 01:09:42.108
Even after 4 years of hiding.
those debt collectors won't give up.

1062
01:09:42.193 --> 01:09:46.403
They're still searching for him.
threatening to stab him.

1063
01:09:46.489 --> 01:09:48.025
You used loan sharks?

1064
01:09:48.908 --> 01:09:50.774
It's all my fault.

1065
01:09:51.369 --> 01:09:52.860
The Taiwan cake shop.

1066
01:09:53.204 --> 01:09:57.244
My Taiwanese Wangshui
castella shop went bust.

1067
01:09:57.775 --> 01:09:59.858
I was overwhelmed by debt.

1068
01:10:00.027 --> 01:10:01.609
Please take this.

1069
01:10:01.946 --> 01:10:03.403
What's that?

1070
01:10:03.572 --> 01:10:07.737
It's not much.
just a modest sum.

1071
01:10:07.827 --> 01:10:10.490
But we'll send it
to you every month.

1072
01:10:11.038 --> 01:10:12.870
In return.
just once every 2 days.

1073
01:10:12.957 --> 01:10:15.950
please leave him some food.

1074
01:10:16.711 --> 01:10:19.624
No no. just once a week.

1075
01:10:20.172 --> 01:10:22.414
There's a refrigerator here.
Just once a week.

1076
01:10:22.508 --> 01:10:25.626
You've got some nerve!
I'm calling the police.

1077
01:10:25.720 --> 01:10:26.720
Sis!

1078
01:10:29.056 --> 01:10:30.342
Who is that?

1079
01:10:33.477 --> 01:10:35.139
Wait... Jessica?

1080
01:10:35.938 --> 01:10:37.099
Mr. Kim?

1081
01:10:37.189 --> 01:10:38.270
What the hell?

1082
01:10:39.608 --> 01:10:40.849
Dad. my ankle!

1083
01:10:40.943 --> 01:10:42.059
You okay?
Sorry.

1084
01:10:42.153 --> 01:10:44.236
Dad. my foot.

1085
01:10:44.321 --> 01:10:46.108
Don't call me Dad!

1086
01:10:53.122 --> 01:10:57.036
I thought it was weird
when the driver was fired.

1087
01:10:57.918 --> 01:10:58.626
Hey!

1088
01:10:58.627 --> 01:11:00.994
- Let's talk things over.
- What the hell?

1089
01:11:01.088 --> 01:11:02.499
Are you some family of charlatans?

1090
01:11:02.590 --> 01:11:03.548
So. sis...

1091
01:11:03.549 --> 01:11:05.836
Don't fucking call me sis.
you filthy bitch!

1092
01:11:06.260 --> 01:11:11.301
I'm gonna send this video
to the madame. how about that?

1093
01:11:11.390 --> 01:11:13.347
<i>Dad. my foot.</i>

1094
01:11:13.559 --> 01:11:15.767
No reception in the basement.
right?

1095
01:11:16.437 --> 01:11:18.303
- The phone works fine.
- Fuck.

1096
01:11:18.397 --> 01:11:23.108
Ma'am. to be honest.
the jobs we have here...

1097
01:11:23.194 --> 01:11:26.107
Shut up!
It's too late now!

1098
01:11:26.197 --> 01:11:29.531
Let's all go to jail!
We're fucking going down!

1099
01:11:29.617 --> 01:11:32.530
Lady. are you crazy?

1100
01:11:33.370 --> 01:11:38.240
If they see that video. Mr. Park
and his wife will be so shocked!

1101
01:11:38.626 --> 01:11:41.790
What did those nice people
ever do wrong?

1102
01:11:42.630 --> 01:11:43.630
Why do this to them?

1103
01:11:43.672 --> 01:11:44.879
Stop right there!

1104
01:11:45.257 --> 01:11:47.374
Or I'll push the 'send' button.

1105
01:11:47.802 --> 01:11:49.168
Follow me.

1106
01:11:49.929 --> 01:11:52.342
Calm down. ma'am.

1107
01:11:55.976 --> 01:11:57.933
Don't push!

1108
01:11:59.188 --> 01:12:00.770
Let's go up. honey.

1109
01:12:01.190 --> 01:12:03.853
Time for you to get some fresh air!

1110
01:12:21.168 --> 01:12:27.165
Honey. this 'send' button is
like a missile launcher.

1111
01:12:27.758 --> 01:12:29.545
What do you mean. honey?

1112
01:12:30.177 --> 01:12:35.297
If we threaten to push it.
those people can't do anything.

1113
01:12:35.432 --> 01:12:39.767
It's like a North Korean rocket.
A North Korean missile button!

1114
01:12:41.188 --> 01:12:44.932
Today our beloved
Great Leader Kim Jong-un.

1115
01:12:45.067 --> 01:12:48.151
after witnessing
the charlatan family video.

1116
01:12:48.237 --> 01:12:50.900
was unable to contain
his shock and fury

1117
01:12:50.990 --> 01:12:54.154
at their wicked.
despicable provocation!

1118
01:12:54.243 --> 01:12:56.200
I've missed your jokes. honey!

1119
01:12:56.287 --> 01:13:00.827
Therefore our Great Leader.
in this age of denuclearization.

1120
01:13:00.916 --> 01:13:06.662
has commanded that the nation's
last remaining nuclear warhead

1121
01:13:06.755 --> 01:13:09.293
be driven down the throats
of this wicked family!

1122
01:13:09.383 --> 01:13:14.048
No one can imitate North Korean
news anchors like you!

1123
01:13:14.138 --> 01:13:19.384
With their stinking guts serving
as the last nuclear graveyard.

1124
01:13:19.476 --> 01:13:24.141
our Dear Leader's wish to denuclearize
and bring world peace can...

1125
01:13:24.231 --> 01:13:26.018
Hands in the air. fuckers!

1126
01:13:26.442 --> 01:13:27.853
Higher!

1127
01:13:29.778 --> 01:13:31.815
You scumbag family.

1128
01:13:31.906 --> 01:13:33.022
Husband?

1129
01:13:33.240 --> 01:13:34.032
Husband.

1130
01:13:34.033 --> 01:13:34.991
Wife?

1131
01:13:34.992 --> 01:13:35.867
Yes.

1132
01:13:35.868 --> 01:13:37.530
- Son?
- Yes.

1133
01:13:37.620 --> 01:13:38.861
- Daughter?
- Daughter.

1134
01:13:38.954 --> 01:13:40.741
You neanderthals.

1135
01:13:41.040 --> 01:13:45.125
Is that all you can think to do.
drink yourselves stupid?

1136
01:13:45.502 --> 01:13:50.543
In this home suffused
with Mr. Namgoong's creative spirit?

1137
01:13:50.799 --> 01:13:51.880
You cretins!

1138
01:13:51.967 --> 01:13:53.333
What do you know about art?

1139
01:13:53.427 --> 01:13:55.544
What would they know?

1140
01:13:56.347 --> 01:14:03.347
When the sun was nice.
we'd bask in those sunbeams. right?

1141
01:14:04.980 --> 01:14:09.270
At such moments we could feel
his artistic touch.

1142
01:14:57.032 --> 01:15:00.366
Give it to me!

1143
01:15:19.555 --> 01:15:23.299
Good job!
Delete it!

1144
01:15:24.143 --> 01:15:27.136
Careful. don't send it by accident.

1145
01:15:42.077 --> 01:15:43.363
Hello?

1146
01:15:43.828 --> 01:15:47.492
Listen. do you know
how to make ram-don?

1147
01:15:47.958 --> 01:15:49.165
Ram-don?

1148
01:15:49.251 --> 01:15:52.665
Da-song likes ram-don
more than anything.

1149
01:15:53.046 --> 01:15:56.460
If you boil the water now.
the timing will be perfect.

1150
01:15:56.883 --> 01:15:59.591
<i>There's sirloin in the fridge.
add that too.</i>

1151
01:15:59.678 --> 01:16:01.294
Then. the camping...?

1152
01:16:01.388 --> 01:16:04.847
<i>My god. what a disaster.</i>

1153
01:16:05.517 --> 01:16:10.683
The river overflowed and
everyone was packing their tents.

1154
01:16:10.939 --> 01:16:13.852
but Da-song was crying
and refusing to go home.

1155
01:16:14.067 --> 01:16:17.936
<i>Anyway. ram-don as soon
as we walk in. okay?</i>

1156
01:16:18.405 --> 01:16:20.738
Then you're almost here?

1157
01:16:20.865 --> 01:16:23.323
8 minutes. according to the GPS.

1158
01:16:23.827 --> 01:16:24.908
You arrive in 8 minutes...

1159
01:16:24.995 --> 01:16:28.488
<i>Start boiling
the water right away!</i>

1160
01:16:32.669 --> 01:16:34.376
What the hell is ram-don?

1161
01:16:43.388 --> 01:16:45.050
Move. quickly!

1162
01:16:46.141 --> 01:16:47.848
Hurry!

1163
01:16:54.774 --> 01:16:56.561
<i>Ramen / Udon</i>

1164
01:16:58.445 --> 01:17:01.153
Dad. I can't drag her any further!

1165
01:17:12.167 --> 01:17:14.033
What are you doing?

1166
01:17:15.587 --> 01:17:17.044
Dad!

1167
01:17:20.383 --> 01:17:23.296
Go up quickly!
Help upstairs.

1168
01:17:31.144 --> 01:17:32.385
Take this!

1169
01:17:51.623 --> 01:17:52.830
Welcome home!

1170
01:17:52.916 --> 01:17:56.284
Da-song. look!
Let's eat ram-don!

1171
01:17:58.338 --> 01:17:59.670
<i>Da-song!</i>

1172
01:18:02.634 --> 01:18:04.500
<i>Da-song!</i>

1173
01:18:10.850 --> 01:18:12.307
Madame!

1174
01:18:30.662 --> 01:18:32.904
Why don't you
just eat the ram-don?

1175
01:18:32.997 --> 01:18:33.914
Shall I?

1176
01:18:33.915 --> 01:18:36.953
No wait. I can give it
to my husband.

1177
01:18:37.043 --> 01:18:38.955
There's sirloin in here.

1178
01:18:41.506 --> 01:18:45.170
It's cooked through?
Medium well done.

1179
01:19:10.368 --> 01:19:16.205
<i>Returning after a day's work...
I love you so much. Mr. Park!</i>

1180
01:19:16.374 --> 01:19:22.541
<i>Home from the office.
Mr. Park is off duty now.</i>

1181
01:19:24.632 --> 01:19:28.922
<i>Returning after a day's work...
I love you so much. Mr. Park!</i>

1182
01:19:29.012 --> 01:19:30.924
- What are you doing?
- Shut up!

1183
01:19:42.484 --> 01:19:44.851
Honey. do you want some ram-don?

1184
01:19:45.111 --> 01:19:46.147
Da-song doesn't want it?

1185
01:19:46.237 --> 01:19:46.945
No.

1186
01:19:46.946 --> 01:19:48.983
No. I'm tired.
I'm going to bed.

1187
01:19:49.240 --> 01:19:51.983
Why are you staring?

1188
01:19:53.203 --> 01:19:56.742
Mr. Park. you feed me
and house me.

1189
01:19:56.831 --> 01:19:58.163
<i>Respect!</i>

1190
01:20:00.251 --> 01:20:01.992
You do this every day?

1191
01:20:02.545 --> 01:20:07.836
Sure. I even send whole sentences
to thank him.

1192
01:20:08.426 --> 01:20:10.668
Someone of your age should know it.

1193
01:20:10.762 --> 01:20:11.762
Know what?

1194
01:20:11.805 --> 01:20:13.421
Morse Code.

1195
01:20:14.098 --> 01:20:17.842
That sensor's going batty.

1196
01:20:26.319 --> 01:20:29.653
Da-song will know it.
since he's a Scout.

1197
01:20:29.906 --> 01:20:31.363
It's ridiculous. right?

1198
01:20:31.741 --> 01:20:34.984
Running around.
trying to please a kid.

1199
01:20:35.286 --> 01:20:37.118
He's not some kind of prince.

1200
01:20:37.372 --> 01:20:39.830
He's the youngest. It's common.

1201
01:20:41.125 --> 01:20:42.661
Please understand.

1202
01:20:43.169 --> 01:20:46.662
Da-song is a bit... unwell.

1203
01:20:47.215 --> 01:20:50.003
He's receiving trauma therapy
and art therapy.

1204
01:20:51.177 --> 01:20:53.134
There was an incident.

1205
01:20:53.263 --> 01:20:54.629
What incident?

1206
01:20:55.056 --> 01:20:58.345
Sis. you believe in ghosts. too?

1207
01:21:00.019 --> 01:21:03.512
Da-song saw a ghost in the house
when he was in 1st grade.

1208
01:21:10.113 --> 01:21:12.696
He had a birthday party
at home that day.

1209
01:21:12.991 --> 01:21:15.449
Late that night.
when everyone was sleeping.

1210
01:21:15.535 --> 01:21:19.779
Da-song crept down to the kitchen
and took the cake out.

1211
01:21:20.206 --> 01:21:23.119
The whipped cream
on that cake was amazing.

1212
01:21:23.334 --> 01:21:25.917
Even in bed. he couldn't stop
thinking about it.

1213
01:21:26.546 --> 01:21:31.917
So Da-song was sitting.
eating his cake...

1214
01:21:41.644 --> 01:21:44.557
He screamed.
and I ran downstairs.

1215
01:21:45.189 --> 01:21:46.976
and he was all...

1216
01:21:47.692 --> 01:21:52.858
his eyes rolled back in his head.
convulsions. foam in his mouth.

1217
01:21:55.033 --> 01:21:57.320
Have you ever seen
a child have a seizure?

1218
01:21:57.410 --> 01:21:58.328
No.

1219
01:21:58.329 --> 01:22:03.289
They need 15-minute treatment.
or they're done for.

1220
01:22:03.583 --> 01:22:07.873
That's the time you have to reach
an emergency room. 15 minutes.

1221
01:22:09.047 --> 01:22:14.509
How can you live
in a place like this?

1222
01:22:14.636 --> 01:22:17.674
Well. lots of people
live underground.

1223
01:22:17.931 --> 01:22:19.797
Especially if you count
semi-basements.

1224
01:22:19.891 --> 01:22:24.181
What'll you do?
You don't have a plan?

1225
01:22:24.729 --> 01:22:27.972
I just feel comfortable here.

1226
01:22:29.400 --> 01:22:32.188
It feels like I was born here.

1227
01:22:33.237 --> 01:22:36.230
Maybe I had my wedding here. too.

1228
01:22:36.699 --> 01:22:39.658
As for the National Pension.
I don't qualify.

1229
01:22:41.120 --> 01:22:44.454
In my old age.
love will comfort me.

1230
01:22:46.250 --> 01:22:51.291
So please.
Let me live down here.

1231
01:22:53.257 --> 01:22:54.589
Anyway...

1232
01:22:55.551 --> 01:23:00.467
My husband was away on business.
so I had to deal with it all.

1233
01:23:01.224 --> 01:23:05.434
Since then we've always
gone out for his birthday.

1234
01:23:05.728 --> 01:23:08.266
Last year my mother's house.
this year. camping.

1235
01:23:08.690 --> 01:23:13.526
Da-song's dad says it's just
a part of growing up.

1236
01:23:13.736 --> 01:23:18.276
They say a ghost
in the house brings wealth.

1237
01:23:19.659 --> 01:23:24.279
Actually. the money's been
good recently.

1238
01:23:51.274 --> 01:23:52.856
Thank god.

1239
01:24:19.510 --> 01:24:22.378
Just stay here for now.

1240
01:24:33.232 --> 01:24:35.098
Zoonie. what's wrong?

1241
01:24:38.237 --> 01:24:39.773
Something under there?

1242
01:24:41.031 --> 01:24:42.488
What is it?

1243
01:24:43.701 --> 01:24:45.033
Damn it!

1244
01:24:46.412 --> 01:24:47.573
- Mom!
- Yeah?

1245
01:24:47.663 --> 01:24:50.030
- How could you?
- What?

1246
01:24:50.124 --> 01:24:54.209
I like ram-don too!
How could you not even ask me?

1247
01:24:54.545 --> 01:24:55.421
Well...

1248
01:24:55.422 --> 01:24:59.210
Da-song didn't want it. so you asked Dad.
then ate it yourself.

1249
01:24:59.300 --> 01:25:00.300
Want her to make one?

1250
01:25:00.342 --> 01:25:02.208
That's not the point!

1251
01:25:02.303 --> 01:25:05.637
- Stop fighting over ramen!
- Why didn't you ask me?

1252
01:25:06.098 --> 01:25:08.715
Oh. stop it! Just go to bed.
Go get changed.

1253
01:25:13.105 --> 01:25:14.471
This way!

1254
01:25:16.609 --> 01:25:17.609
And Ki-jung?

1255
01:25:17.693 --> 01:25:20.060
Under there! Hurry!

1256
01:25:22.406 --> 01:25:25.990
One. two. three! One. two three!

1257
01:25:26.076 --> 01:25:27.362
Da-song?

1258
01:25:28.370 --> 01:25:29.906
Da-song. cut it out!

1259
01:25:30.414 --> 01:25:33.157
He's gone crazy!
Get an umbrella.

1260
01:25:33.459 --> 01:25:34.995
Hey Park Da-song!

1261
01:25:36.503 --> 01:25:40.713
What a monster.
What the hell is he doing?

1262
01:25:41.425 --> 01:25:45.169
Da-song. it's time for bed!
You know how late it is?

1263
01:25:45.262 --> 01:25:46.423
Here.

1264
01:25:47.264 --> 01:25:48.721
Honey. here.

1265
01:25:53.687 --> 01:25:58.728
Who do you take after to be so stubborn!
Look at this rain!

1266
01:26:04.156 --> 01:26:06.864
<i>OMG Kevin. Da-song camping
in the yard.</i>

1267
01:26:10.829 --> 01:26:15.119
Hey. channel 3 for emergencies!
Keep it turned on.

1268
01:26:15.751 --> 01:26:18.494
Let me have it.
I can't believe him.

1269
01:26:19.088 --> 01:26:21.671
Just leave him.
He'll come in if he's tired.

1270
01:26:21.882 --> 01:26:24.670
<i>- I want you here. honey.
- I'm with you.</i>

1271
01:26:24.760 --> 01:26:26.001
Hey. Da-hye!

1272
01:26:26.095 --> 01:26:28.553
Stop using your phone.
Go to bed.

1273
01:26:28.972 --> 01:26:31.510
Go sleep in your room.
We'll take care of things.

1274
01:26:31.642 --> 01:26:34.931
This is the living room.
do you copy?

1275
01:26:35.020 --> 01:26:36.101
<i>Copy. over.</i>

1276
01:26:36.188 --> 01:26:40.148
Daddy is standing by
for emergencies. over.

1277
01:26:40.275 --> 01:26:42.767
<i>Got it. over.</i>

1278
01:26:44.113 --> 01:26:46.150
Is that tent going to leak?

1279
01:26:46.240 --> 01:26:49.483
We ordered from the U.S..
it'll be fine.

1280
01:26:49.660 --> 01:26:52.619
- Should we sleep here?
- What?

1281
01:26:52.746 --> 01:26:54.954
We've got a full view of the tent.

1282
01:26:55.082 --> 01:26:56.948
Good idea.
I'll feel much better.

1283
01:26:57.042 --> 01:26:57.834
Right?

1284
01:26:57.835 --> 01:26:59.827
Let's watch over him as we sleep.

1285
01:27:01.964 --> 01:27:03.455
What a kid...

1286
01:27:12.683 --> 01:27:14.049
Wait a minute.

1287
01:27:16.478 --> 01:27:18.640
Where's that smell coming from?

1288
01:27:18.731 --> 01:27:20.017
What smell?

1289
01:27:20.315 --> 01:27:21.772
Mr. Kim's smell.

1290
01:27:22.234 --> 01:27:23.770
- Mr. Kim?
- Yeah.

1291
01:27:24.570 --> 01:27:25.936
Not sure what you mean.

1292
01:27:26.029 --> 01:27:28.988
Really?
You must have smelled it.

1293
01:27:29.366 --> 01:27:33.326
That smell that wafts through the car.
how to describe it?

1294
01:27:33.412 --> 01:27:36.155
- An old man's smell?
- No no. it's not that.

1295
01:27:36.248 --> 01:27:37.955
What is it?

1296
01:27:38.584 --> 01:27:40.576
Like an old radish?

1297
01:27:41.170 --> 01:27:42.251
No.

1298
01:27:42.546 --> 01:27:44.788
You know when you boil a rag?

1299
01:27:44.882 --> 01:27:46.293
It smells like that.

1300
01:27:48.802 --> 01:27:55.174
Anyway. even though he always seems
about to cross the line.

1301
01:27:55.267 --> 01:27:58.351
he never does cross it.
That's good.

1302
01:27:58.562 --> 01:28:00.269
- I'll give him credit.
- Yeah.

1303
01:28:01.398 --> 01:28:03.685
But that smell crosses the line.

1304
01:28:04.276 --> 01:28:06.563
It powers through right
into the back seat.

1305
01:28:06.945 --> 01:28:08.686
How bad can it be?

1306
01:28:08.781 --> 01:28:10.022
I don't know.

1307
01:28:10.741 --> 01:28:13.233
It's hard to describe.

1308
01:28:14.244 --> 01:28:17.863
But you sometimes smell it
on the subway.

1309
01:28:17.998 --> 01:28:21.241
It's been ages
since I rode a subway.

1310
01:28:21.960 --> 01:28:24.919
People who ride the subway
have a special smell.

1311
01:28:25.005 --> 01:28:26.212
Yeah.

1312
01:28:42.564 --> 01:28:45.147
Isn't this like the car's back seat?

1313
01:28:45.734 --> 01:28:49.523
What if Da-song comes back in?

1314
01:28:50.155 --> 01:28:51.646
Don't worry!

1315
01:28:52.241 --> 01:28:54.904
I can just pull my hand back.

1316
01:29:00.541 --> 01:29:02.032
We shouldn't...

1317
01:29:08.131 --> 01:29:09.793
Do it clockwise.

1318
01:29:10.509 --> 01:29:11.670
Right.

1319
01:29:15.055 --> 01:29:17.843
You know where.

1320
01:29:34.741 --> 01:29:38.405
You still have those cheap panties?

1321
01:29:38.829 --> 01:29:39.865
Huh?

1322
01:29:39.997 --> 01:29:42.785
The ones Yoon's girlfriend left behind.

1323
01:29:43.917 --> 01:29:46.910
If you wear those.
I'll get really fucking hard.

1324
01:29:47.671 --> 01:29:49.003
Really?

1325
01:29:49.464 --> 01:29:52.002
Then buy me drugs.

1326
01:29:53.051 --> 01:29:55.794
Buy me drugs!

1327
01:29:57.681 --> 01:29:59.263
Eat this instead.

1328
01:30:11.111 --> 01:30:12.647
You like it?

1329
01:30:33.300 --> 01:30:35.417
<i>They're passed out cold.
Sneak out now.</i>

1330
01:31:09.586 --> 01:31:12.044
<i>Emergency! Emergency. over!</i>

1331
01:31:14.341 --> 01:31:15.923
<i>- Emergency!</i>
- What?

1332
01:31:16.843 --> 01:31:18.084
What is it. over!

1333
01:31:18.303 --> 01:31:19.464
Da-song. what's wrong?

1334
01:31:20.013 --> 01:31:22.096
<i>I can't sleep. over.</i>

1335
01:31:22.516 --> 01:31:26.226
So stop it and come in. okay?

1336
01:31:26.561 --> 01:31:29.099
Go sleep in your soft bed. over.

1337
01:31:29.272 --> 01:31:30.558
Right!

1338
01:31:30.774 --> 01:31:32.857
<i>I don't want to. over.</i>

1339
01:31:33.360 --> 01:31:34.817
Hey. Park Da-song.

1340
01:31:39.783 --> 01:31:41.615
Let's just sleep...

1341
01:33:17.672 --> 01:33:21.211
How did it turn out back there?

1342
01:33:22.176 --> 01:33:23.417
What?

1343
01:33:25.597 --> 01:33:27.714
The people in the basement.

1344
01:33:30.602 --> 01:33:34.767
Well. I tied them up.

1345
01:33:35.106 --> 01:33:37.063
What will we do now?

1346
01:33:38.526 --> 01:33:39.767
Huh?

1347
01:33:41.904 --> 01:33:45.068
What do we do now.
what's our plan?

1348
01:33:46.075 --> 01:33:48.909
I've been wondering...

1349
01:33:49.787 --> 01:33:52.951
What would Min do
in this situation?

1350
01:33:54.667 --> 01:33:57.455
Min wouldn't be
in this situation!

1351
01:33:59.005 --> 01:34:04.672
Look kids. we made it
out of there safely. right?

1352
01:34:05.970 --> 01:34:11.056
And besides us. nobody knows
what happened there. Right?

1353
01:34:11.476 --> 01:34:13.934
So nothing happened.
You understand?

1354
01:34:15.355 --> 01:34:19.725
I've got my own plan.

1355
01:34:20.318 --> 01:34:23.186
So you two just forget
about it. okay?

1356
01:34:24.530 --> 01:34:26.522
Let's go home.

1357
01:34:27.116 --> 01:34:29.073
Let's go take a bath.

1358
01:34:48.012 --> 01:34:50.379
What are you doing there?
Hurry up!

1359
01:35:04.821 --> 01:35:06.562
What's going on?

1360
01:35:08.366 --> 01:35:11.074
You stay there.
This is all sewage water.

1361
01:35:11.244 --> 01:35:14.078
Was our window open?

1362
01:35:18.126 --> 01:35:21.210
Help me out. Ki-taek!

1363
01:35:29.429 --> 01:35:30.795
Ki-woo!

1364
01:35:33.099 --> 01:35:35.887
Hey Ki-woo. close the window!

1365
01:35:37.854 --> 01:35:39.140
You got shocked?

1366
01:35:46.028 --> 01:35:47.519
I'm dizzy.

1367
01:35:51.409 --> 01:35:55.073
Hold on a sec.
Wait.

1368
01:36:00.877 --> 01:36:02.584
Shit. I'm dizzy.

1369
01:36:06.799 --> 01:36:09.086
Ki-jung. be careful.

1370
01:36:10.803 --> 01:36:12.590
Don't touch anything.

1371
01:36:24.650 --> 01:36:30.396
Honey. I've got a concussion.

1372
01:36:30.698 --> 01:36:33.190
I can't see you.

1373
01:36:54.639 --> 01:36:59.054
Honey. that woman Chung-sook...

1374
01:36:59.936 --> 01:37:01.848
Oh. god.

1375
01:37:02.021 --> 01:37:04.013
What a nice person.

1376
01:37:05.858 --> 01:37:08.851
She kicked me down the stairs.

1377
01:37:11.447 --> 01:37:13.439
Repeat after me.

1378
01:37:14.242 --> 01:37:16.404
Chung-sook...

1379
01:37:18.371 --> 01:37:21.284
Chung-sook...

1380
01:37:30.967 --> 01:37:32.833
Hey. Ki-woo!

1381
01:37:34.136 --> 01:37:35.672
What are you doing there?

1382
01:37:35.763 --> 01:37:37.004
Huh?

1383
01:37:51.737 --> 01:37:55.606
<i>h o l p... M...</i>

1384
01:39:01.265 --> 01:39:02.426
Dad.

1385
01:39:03.059 --> 01:39:04.220
Yeah?

1386
01:39:05.311 --> 01:39:08.804
What was your plan?

1387
01:39:10.733 --> 01:39:12.520
What are you talking about?

1388
01:39:13.653 --> 01:39:16.236
Before. you said you had a plan.

1389
01:39:16.614 --> 01:39:18.776
What will you do?
About...

1390
01:39:19.575 --> 01:39:20.861
the basement.

1391
01:39:21.577 --> 01:39:27.323
Ki-woo. you know
what kind of plan never fails?

1392
01:39:29.210 --> 01:39:31.452
No plan at all.

1393
01:39:31.796 --> 01:39:33.253
<i>No plan.</i>

1394
01:39:34.006 --> 01:39:35.463
You know why?

1395
01:39:37.301 --> 01:39:43.673
If you make a plan.
life never works out that way.

1396
01:39:44.642 --> 01:39:46.224
Look around us.

1397
01:39:46.644 --> 01:39:52.060
Did these people think.
"Let's all spend the night in a gym?"

1398
01:39:53.384 --> 01:39:55.000
But look now.

1399
01:39:55.469 --> 01:39:59.088
Everyone's sleeping on the floor.
us included.

1400
01:40:01.016 --> 01:40:04.054
That's why people shouldn't make plans.

1401
01:40:06.230 --> 01:40:10.065
With no plan.
nothing can go wrong.

1402
01:40:10.359 --> 01:40:16.856
And if something spins out of control.
it doesn't matter.

1403
01:40:18.117 --> 01:40:20.860
Whether you kill someone.
or betray your country.

1404
01:40:22.496 --> 01:40:26.080
None of it fucking matters.
Got it?

1405
01:40:28.127 --> 01:40:29.459
Dad.

1406
01:40:31.547 --> 01:40:32.913
I'm sorry.

1407
01:40:33.757 --> 01:40:35.214
For what?

1408
01:40:38.554 --> 01:40:39.920
Everything.

1409
01:40:40.973 --> 01:40:42.384
All of it.

1410
01:40:44.726 --> 01:40:46.433
I'll take care of everything.

1411
01:40:47.646 --> 01:40:49.478
What are you talking about?

1412
01:40:51.817 --> 01:40:54.184
Why are you hugging that stone?

1413
01:40:55.154 --> 01:40:56.486
This?

1414
01:41:02.244 --> 01:41:05.078
It keeps clinging to me.

1415
01:41:09.751 --> 01:41:11.743
I think you need some sleep.

1416
01:41:14.631 --> 01:41:16.088
I'm serious.

1417
01:41:18.010 --> 01:41:20.093
It keeps following me.

1418
01:41:32.774 --> 01:41:35.482
Miss Jessica! Sorry to call
on Sunday morning.

1419
01:41:35.694 --> 01:41:37.981
Are you free for lunch today?

1420
01:41:38.071 --> 01:41:41.906
<i>We're having a birthday impromptu
for Da-song.</i>

1421
01:41:43.452 --> 01:41:45.193
A birthday party?

1422
01:41:45.287 --> 01:41:48.496
If you come too.
Da-song will be so happy.

1423
01:41:48.957 --> 01:41:52.667
And have as much pasta. gratin.
and salmon steak as you want.

1424
01:41:53.128 --> 01:41:55.211
<i>Please come by 1PM.</i>

1425
01:41:55.297 --> 01:41:58.256
and I'll count today
as one of your lessons.

1426
01:41:58.342 --> 01:42:01.005
You know what I mean?
See you soon!

1427
01:42:02.346 --> 01:42:03.803
- Mom.
- Yeah?

1428
01:42:03.889 --> 01:42:07.508
For the impromptu.
should we invite Kevin too?

1429
01:42:07.601 --> 01:42:10.309
Great idea! Why not?
Will you call him?

1430
01:42:10.521 --> 01:42:14.310
Get some more sleep. honey!
You must be tired after yesterday.

1431
01:42:14.525 --> 01:42:18.519
If we have a party.
won't you need to do the rounds?

1432
01:42:18.695 --> 01:42:22.860
Right. the wine shop.
supermarket. bakery. florist...

1433
01:42:23.075 --> 01:42:26.443
But I already told Mr. Kim
to hurry over.

1434
01:42:26.787 --> 01:42:28.198
I'll pay him overtime.

1435
01:42:28.288 --> 01:42:29.288
Perfect

1436
01:42:39.716 --> 01:42:43.881
Everyone sit down.
I'll explain!

1437
01:42:43.971 --> 01:42:47.135
<i>Da-hye: We're having a party.</i>

1438
01:42:47.140 --> 01:42:49.382
<i>and mom said to invite you!</i>

1439
01:42:51.687 --> 01:42:54.680
<i>Sis. in the basement...</i>

1440
01:42:55.065 --> 01:42:57.398
we have 10 outdoor tables.

1441
01:42:57.484 --> 01:43:01.319
First take them all out.
then arrange them...

1442
01:43:01.989 --> 01:43:05.073
No. come to the window.
I need to show you.

1443
01:43:06.910 --> 01:43:08.742
With Da-song's tent
in the middle.

1444
01:43:08.870 --> 01:43:12.238
curve the tables outward...

1445
01:43:12.666 --> 01:43:14.407
A crane's wing formation!

1446
01:43:14.793 --> 01:43:17.911
Like Admiral Yi used. you know?
The Battle of Hansan Island!

1447
01:43:18.338 --> 01:43:20.671
Think of the tent
as the Japanese warship.

1448
01:43:20.757 --> 01:43:26.048
And our tables will make
a semicircular crane's wing formation.

1449
01:43:26.138 --> 01:43:30.303
Then near the tent will be
the barbeque grill. firewood and such.

1450
01:43:30.392 --> 01:43:32.384
Arrange them all there!

1451
01:43:32.978 --> 01:43:36.346
Oh sure. bring your husband too!

1452
01:43:36.440 --> 01:43:37.440
Yeah.

1453
01:43:37.524 --> 01:43:41.108
And definitely no presents.
just come!

1454
01:43:41.194 --> 01:43:41.986
Yeah.

1455
01:43:42.287 --> 01:43:44.324
What dress code?

1456
01:43:44.414 --> 01:43:47.748
It's an impromptu.
You can wear sweat pants!

1457
01:43:48.919 --> 01:43:54.790
And definitely no presents!
Just come and eat hors d'oeuvres!

1458
01:43:55.884 --> 01:43:57.841
You know my culinary skills!

1459
01:43:58.094 --> 01:44:02.805
Right! We'll get drunk
in the daytime.

1460
01:44:03.266 --> 01:44:04.266
Yeah.

1461
01:44:04.351 --> 01:44:08.186
If you'd sing. that'd be grand!
You know the one...

1462
01:44:23.995 --> 01:44:26.863
Quiet. he's sleeping!

1463
01:44:27.290 --> 01:44:30.499
Today the sky's so blue.
and no pollution!

1464
01:44:30.835 --> 01:44:32.872
Thanks to all the rain yesterday.

1465
01:44:34.047 --> 01:44:35.163
Right.

1466
01:44:35.382 --> 01:44:39.171
So we traded camping
for a garden party.

1467
01:44:40.470 --> 01:44:41.881
Lemons into lemonade.

1468
01:44:45.266 --> 01:44:50.057
Right. that rain was such
a blessing!

1469
01:44:51.648 --> 01:44:56.109
And definitely no presents.
I mean it!

1470
01:44:56.861 --> 01:45:00.480
Right. just squeeze
your Mini Cooper into the garage.

1471
01:45:00.573 --> 01:45:02.155
Go on up!

1472
01:45:02.283 --> 01:45:07.403
Right. back it in.
Just don't block the Benz!

1473
01:45:07.497 --> 01:45:11.741
You're here!
It's been so long!

1474
01:45:12.836 --> 01:45:15.328
I told you no presents!

1475
01:45:33.732 --> 01:45:35.564
You were thinking of something else.

1476
01:45:36.067 --> 01:45:37.308
What?

1477
01:45:38.278 --> 01:45:41.737
While kissing me.
you thought of something else.

1478
01:45:43.783 --> 01:45:44.899
No.

1479
01:45:45.785 --> 01:45:49.278
What do you mean?
You're doing it now. too.

1480
01:45:52.000 --> 01:45:53.241
Wow.

1481
01:45:55.128 --> 01:45:57.415
Everyone looks gorgeous. right?

1482
01:45:59.007 --> 01:46:02.671
Even for a sudden gathering.
they're so cool.

1483
01:46:04.012 --> 01:46:05.844
And look so natural.

1484
01:46:07.932 --> 01:46:09.264
Da-hye.

1485
01:46:12.020 --> 01:46:13.477
Do I fit in here?

1486
01:46:15.231 --> 01:46:16.472
What?

1487
01:46:17.442 --> 01:46:20.276
In this setting. do I fit in?

1488
01:46:30.622 --> 01:46:32.614
Hey. where are you going?

1489
01:46:33.124 --> 01:46:34.490
I need to go down.

1490
01:46:34.751 --> 01:46:36.993
Just stay with me.

1491
01:46:38.129 --> 01:46:39.836
I need to go down there.

1492
01:46:40.590 --> 01:46:45.085
Why go to those boring people?
Can't you stay here?

1493
01:46:46.054 --> 01:46:50.389
Not to those people. down lower.

1494
01:46:50.934 --> 01:46:53.426
Wow. what is that?

1495
01:46:56.689 --> 01:47:00.308
God. I can't believe
I'm doing this at my age.

1496
01:47:01.027 --> 01:47:02.893
It's so embarrassing.

1497
01:47:03.947 --> 01:47:05.654
I'm really sorry. Mr. Kim.

1498
01:47:05.824 --> 01:47:08.908
Da-song's mom insisted.
it can't be helped.

1499
01:47:09.119 --> 01:47:10.781
But the concept is simple.

1500
01:47:10.870 --> 01:47:16.116
There'll be a parade with Jessica
carrying a birthday cake.

1501
01:47:16.209 --> 01:47:20.169
Then we jump out and attack Jessica.

1502
01:47:20.255 --> 01:47:22.292
Swinging our tomahawks!

1503
01:47:22.549 --> 01:47:23.507
Right.

1504
01:47:23.508 --> 01:47:28.469
Just then. Da-song the good Indian
will jump out and we'll do battle.

1505
01:47:29.180 --> 01:47:33.470
Finally he'll save Jessica the cake princess.
and they'll all cheer.

1506
01:47:33.726 --> 01:47:35.342
Something like that.

1507
01:47:36.521 --> 01:47:37.521
Silly. isn't it?

1508
01:47:37.564 --> 01:47:42.355
I guess your wife likes events
and surprises.

1509
01:47:42.485 --> 01:47:44.147
Yeah. she does.

1510
01:47:44.571 --> 01:47:47.279
But she's particularly
into this party.

1511
01:47:48.950 --> 01:47:51.818
You're trying your best. too.

1512
01:47:53.121 --> 01:47:55.829
Well. you love her. after all.

1513
01:48:01.421 --> 01:48:02.753
Mr. Kim.

1514
01:48:04.465 --> 01:48:06.752
You're getting paid extra.

1515
01:48:12.223 --> 01:48:16.217
Think of this as part of your work.
okay?

1516
01:48:27.906 --> 01:48:29.397
Did you go down below?

1517
01:48:29.574 --> 01:48:33.363
- Not yet.
- Shouldn't we talk to them?

1518
01:48:33.453 --> 01:48:35.160
Reach an understanding?

1519
01:48:35.288 --> 01:48:36.369
Exactly!

1520
01:48:36.456 --> 01:48:39.039
We all got too fucking worked up
last night.

1521
01:48:39.125 --> 01:48:42.869
Dad was going on about some plan...

1522
01:48:43.546 --> 01:48:46.038
- I'm just going down there.
- Hold on.

1523
01:48:46.132 --> 01:48:48.374
Take this down to them.

1524
01:48:48.468 --> 01:48:50.084
- They must be hungry.
- Right.

1525
01:48:50.178 --> 01:48:51.760
Let them eat first.

1526
01:48:52.889 --> 01:48:54.755
Come next time for sure!

1527
01:48:56.351 --> 01:48:58.388
Here you are. Jessica.

1528
01:48:58.519 --> 01:49:00.761
- This is so amazing.
- Isn't it great?

1529
01:49:00.939 --> 01:49:03.352
I've got a special favor to ask.

1530
01:49:03.483 --> 01:49:04.599
What is it?

1531
01:49:04.734 --> 01:49:07.021
This is... how to describe it?

1532
01:49:07.111 --> 01:49:09.068
Da-song's trauma recovery cake?

1533
01:49:09.155 --> 01:49:12.273
So it needs to be you who does it.
Today's highlight!

1534
01:50:35.325 --> 01:50:38.534
Hey. are you okay?

1535
01:50:43.916 --> 01:50:45.248
Are you...?

1536
01:50:55.178 --> 01:50:56.669
Wait. mister!

1537
01:52:43.619 --> 01:52:46.327
Kevin? Kevin!

1538
01:52:53.212 --> 01:52:56.046
Da-song. happy birthday!

1539
01:52:56.132 --> 01:52:57.418
Congratulations!

1540
01:53:04.849 --> 01:53:06.010
Shit...

1541
01:53:16.068 --> 01:53:17.525
<i>Stop!</i>

1542
01:53:18.070 --> 01:53:20.153
Chung-sook!

1543
01:53:20.239 --> 01:53:21.198
Ki-jung!

1544
01:53:21.199 --> 01:53:22.485
Come out here. Chung-sook!

1545
01:53:22.575 --> 01:53:26.114
Stop the blood! Push down
on the wound!

1546
01:53:30.958 --> 01:53:32.074
Da-song!

1547
01:53:32.793 --> 01:53:33.874
Honey!

1548
01:53:35.463 --> 01:53:37.295
Let go. don't!

1549
01:53:48.100 --> 01:53:49.466
It hurts.

1550
01:53:54.690 --> 01:53:55.726
The emergency room!

1551
01:53:55.816 --> 01:53:57.057
Get the car!

1552
01:53:57.151 --> 01:53:59.063
Mr. Kim!
What are you doing?

1553
01:53:59.237 --> 01:54:01.229
We can't wait for an ambulance!

1554
01:54:01.322 --> 01:54:03.609
Stop pushing. Dad!

1555
01:54:03.783 --> 01:54:06.617
Makes it hurt more.

1556
01:54:07.370 --> 01:54:08.577
Car keys!
The car keys!

1557
01:54:08.663 --> 01:54:11.155
Throw them!
Throw me the keys!

1558
01:54:29.058 --> 01:54:30.390
Are you okay?

1559
01:54:30.935 --> 01:54:32.392
Don't touch it!

1560
01:54:34.897 --> 01:54:37.184
Hello. Mr. Park.

1561
01:54:37.400 --> 01:54:38.561
You know me?

1562
01:54:38.651 --> 01:54:39.983
Respect!

1563
01:56:06.947 --> 01:56:10.315
<i>Opening my eyes for the first time
in a month.</i>

1564
01:56:10.409 --> 01:56:11.991
<i>I saw a detective.</i>

1565
01:56:12.286 --> 01:56:17.077
You have the right to
an attorney...

1566
01:56:17.166 --> 01:56:19.283
<i>Who looked nothing like
a detective.</i>

1567
01:56:23.756 --> 01:56:25.418
Is he laughing?

1568
01:56:25.841 --> 01:56:27.298
Just a sec.

1569
01:56:27.885 --> 01:56:32.346
<i>Then the doctor who looked
nothing like a doctor spoke.</i>

1570
01:56:33.724 --> 01:56:37.434
That happens sometimes
after brain surgery.

1571
01:56:37.645 --> 01:56:39.511
They keep laughing.
For no reason.

1572
01:56:40.439 --> 01:56:42.522
Do you hear me?

1573
01:56:42.942 --> 01:56:44.649
Can you hear me?

1574
01:56:44.944 --> 01:56:46.685
Then do I have to do it again?

1575
01:56:46.821 --> 01:56:47.737
Do what?

1576
01:56:47.738 --> 01:56:49.274
The Miranda thing.

1577
01:56:51.534 --> 01:56:55.869
You have the right to remain silent.

1578
01:56:55.955 --> 01:56:58.572
Anything you say can and
will be used against you...

1579
01:56:58.666 --> 01:57:00.578
He keeps laughing. look!

1580
01:57:03.963 --> 01:57:09.800
<i>Even when I heard
how much Ki-jung bled that day...</i>

1581
01:57:12.221 --> 01:57:19.221
<i>Even when I heard the words forgery.
trespassing. foul play. self-defense</i>

1582
01:57:19.729 --> 01:57:23.848
<i>and we were lucky
to get away with a probation...</i>

1583
01:57:27.069 --> 01:57:30.233
<i>Even when I finally
got to see Ki-jung's face...</i>

1584
01:57:30.322 --> 01:57:32.939
<i>Kim Ki-jung. RIP</i>

1585
01:57:34.660 --> 01:57:36.777
<i>I kept laughing.</i>

1586
01:57:46.756 --> 01:57:52.002
<i>Still. when I went back
and watched the news reports.</i>

1587
01:57:52.344 --> 01:57:53.755
<i>I didn't laugh.</i>

1588
01:57:53.804 --> 01:57:57.673
This sudden rampage in the back yard
of an upper-class home

1589
01:57:57.767 --> 01:57:59.383
is a highly unusual case.

1590
01:57:59.477 --> 01:58:03.972
Since the homeless man who sparked
the rampage died at the scene.

1591
01:58:04.064 --> 01:58:09.310
police are struggling to
even establish a clear motive.

1592
01:58:09.403 --> 01:58:13.898
The driver Kim and the slain Mr. Park
are said to have been on good terms.

1593
01:58:14.033 --> 01:58:19.370
For now the police investigation is
focused on locating the driver Kim.

1594
01:58:19.914 --> 01:58:23.703
Kim. after exiting this door
and descending the stairs.

1595
01:58:24.001 --> 01:58:27.119
disappeared into the neighboring alleys.

1596
01:58:27.922 --> 01:58:32.917
Police searched the CCTVs
of nearby homes to no avail.

1597
01:58:33.385 --> 01:58:36.549
and they have yet
to find any witnesses.

1598
01:58:37.097 --> 01:58:39.214
Given the situation.

1599
01:58:39.433 --> 01:58:44.349
it's not an exaggeration to say that
Kim vanished into thin air.

1600
01:58:46.615 --> 01:58:53.579
<i>Actually Mom and I had no idea
where Dad was.</i>

1601
01:58:55.915 --> 01:59:01.286
<i>But those detectives
still wore themselves out tailing us.</i>

1602
01:59:05.425 --> 01:59:09.135
<i>Eventually the news went quiet.</i>

1603
01:59:09.137 --> 01:59:11.254
<i>and after the tails stopped.</i>

1604
01:59:12.057 --> 01:59:15.221
<i>I started going up that mountain.</i>

1605
01:59:17.479 --> 01:59:21.940
<i>From up there.
you get a great view of the house.</i>

1606
01:59:24.986 --> 01:59:28.696
<i>That day. despite the cold.</i>

1607
01:59:29.574 --> 01:59:32.112
<i>I felt like staying longer.</i>

1608
01:59:45.215 --> 01:59:48.253
Dash-dash-dot-dot

1609
02:00:14.035 --> 02:00:15.321
Son!

1610
02:00:17.414 --> 02:00:18.655
<i>Son!</i>

1611
02:00:20.917 --> 02:00:24.331
<i>Perhaps you. if no one else.
will be able to read this letter.</i>

1612
02:00:28.007 --> 02:00:30.590
<i>You were a Boy Scout.</i>

1613
02:00:30.593 --> 02:00:34.052
<i>so I'm writing this just
in case.</i>

1614
02:00:37.600 --> 02:00:40.183
<i>Have your injuries healed?</i>

1615
02:00:41.438 --> 02:00:45.523
<i>I'm sure your mom is
plenty healthy.</i>

1616
02:00:49.654 --> 02:00:52.317
<i>I'm doing fine in here.</i>

1617
02:00:53.533 --> 02:00:56.116
<i>Though thinking of
Ki-jung makes me cry.</i>

1618
02:00:59.581 --> 02:01:03.951
<i>Even now. what happened that day
doesn't seem real.</i>

1619
02:01:05.462 --> 02:01:07.499
<i>It feels like a dream.</i>

1620
02:01:08.798 --> 02:01:10.380
<i>and yet it doesn't.</i>

1621
02:01:11.885 --> 02:01:16.220
<i>That day as I went out the gate.
I suddenly knew.</i>

1622
02:01:17.599 --> 02:01:19.386
<i>Where I needed to go...</i>

1623
02:01:59.015 --> 02:02:02.008
<i>A house where such
a grisly crime took place</i>

1624
02:02:02.143 --> 02:02:04.931
<i>would surely not be easy
to sell.</i>

1625
02:02:08.483 --> 02:02:10.850
I'm sorry. Mr. Park.

1626
02:02:11.027 --> 02:02:17.115
<i>I struggled to hold out like that
in an empty house.</i>

1627
02:02:20.036 --> 02:02:22.949
<i>Still. thanks to the house
being empty.</i>

1628
02:02:23.122 --> 02:02:27.913
<i>what was her name?
Moon-gwang?</i>

1629
02:02:28.127 --> 02:02:31.916
<i>I was able to give her
a proper send off.</i>

1630
02:02:33.508 --> 02:02:39.721
<i>I hear tree-side burials are trendy.
so hell. I did my best.</i>

1631
02:02:43.476 --> 02:02:47.015
<i>But those real estate
sharks sure are clever.</i>

1632
02:02:51.651 --> 02:02:56.112
<i>They hoodwinked some people
who hadjust arrived in Korea</i>

1633
02:02:56.197 --> 02:02:58.405
<i>and managed to sell the house.</i>

1634
02:02:59.617 --> 02:03:02.860
<i>With the parents working.
and the kids attending school.</i>

1635
02:03:02.954 --> 02:03:05.241
<i>the family is usually out.</i>

1636
02:03:05.707 --> 02:03:10.827
<i>But the goddamned housekeeper
stays there 24 hours a day.</i>

1637
02:03:11.296 --> 02:03:15.916
<i>Each time I go upstairs.
I take my life in my hands.</i>

1638
02:03:18.720 --> 02:03:22.805
<i>It turns out Germans eat
more than just sausage and beer.</i>

1639
02:03:23.474 --> 02:03:25.340
<i>What a relief.</i>

1640
02:03:28.229 --> 02:03:32.064
<i>Passing the time down here.
everything starts to go hazy.</i>

1641
02:03:36.863 --> 02:03:40.982
<i>Today at least I was able
to write you a letter.</i>

1642
02:03:42.869 --> 02:03:46.863
<i>If I send out the letter
this way every night.</i>

1643
02:03:46.956 --> 02:03:50.996
<i>maybe someday you'll see it.</i>

1644
02:03:57.175 --> 02:03:58.837
<i>So long.</i>

1645
02:04:12.899 --> 02:04:14.140
You're home. Ki-woo?

1646
02:04:14.233 --> 02:04:15.233
Yeah.

1647
02:04:29.499 --> 02:04:34.164
<i>Dad. today I made a plan.</i>

1648
02:04:35.880 --> 02:04:37.792
<i>A fundamental plan.</i>

1649
02:04:40.885 --> 02:04:42.717
<i>I'm going to earn money.</i>

1650
02:04:43.471 --> 02:04:45.087
<i>A lot of it.</i>

1651
02:04:48.476 --> 02:04:52.891
<i>University. a career. marriage.
those are all fine.</i>

1652
02:04:53.398 --> 02:04:55.355
<i>but first I'll earn money.</i>

1653
02:04:55.483 --> 02:05:00.524
You'll see once you go in.
but it's very spacious.

1654
02:05:01.447 --> 02:05:05.942
Actually. we don't show this house
to just anyone.

1655
02:05:06.327 --> 02:05:10.367
<i>When I have money.
I'll buy that house.</i>

1656
02:05:11.624 --> 02:05:15.834
<i>On the day we move in.
Mom and I will be in the yard.</i>

1657
02:05:16.462 --> 02:05:18.795
<i>Because the sunshine is
so nice there.</i>

1658
02:05:20.133 --> 02:05:21.965
<i>All you'll need to do</i>

1659
02:05:22.385 --> 02:05:24.718
<i>is walk up the stairs.</i>

1660
02:06:47.929 --> 02:06:51.548
<i>Take care until then.</i>

1661
02:06:56.729 --> 02:06:58.391
<i>So long.</i>

1661
02:06:59.305 --> 02:07:59.457
